title: bourbon balls
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, melt the chopped chocolate over low heat, stirring almost constantly to prevent the bottom from scorching.
Remove the pan from the heat and let the chocolate cool to lukewarm.
Combine the vanilla wafer crumbs, pecans and 2/3 cup of sugar in a deep bowl.
Pour in the chocolate, bourbon and corn syrup.
Stir vigorously with a wooden spoon until the ingredients are well combined.
Shape mixture into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll the balls in the remaining sugar and place them in a wide mouthed 1-quart jar with a secure lid.

title: heavenly delight punch
directions: Empty the pineapple juice in a large bowl.
Add the frozen orange juice.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to keep cool. Immediately before serving, add the sorbet; mix well.
Add the 2-quarts of ginger ale just before serving.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Mix and set aside to jell:
water, Jell-O and strawberries. Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 4 ounces Cool Whip and pour onto graham cracker crust.
Next top with Jell-O mixture.
Garnish with remainder of Cool Whip and chopped pecans, if desired.

title: pinch bread
directions: Pinch bread into small pieces and place in loaf pan.
Combine parsley, salt, garlic salt and egg; beat with fork.
Pour over pinched bread.
(Do not let bread rise.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: low calorie spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Package in airtight containers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Combine 2 heaping teaspoonfuls mix with 1 cup boiling water.
Makes a 12-quart drink.

title: mushroom potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes
and slice medium thin.
Cook potatoes (salt to taste) on stovetop until firm, but done.
In saucepan put soup, butter, cream and 4 cheese slices and slowly melt cheese. Drain potatoes and pour in baking dish.
Cover with cheese sauce; top with cheese slices and bake in oven until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and smooth into pan.
Cover and freeze.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray cake pan well with Pam.
Put pecans and coconut into bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions; pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and melted margarine; pour over cake batter.
Mixture may be stiff and need to be dropped by spoonfuls on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken - pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and rinse with cold water. In large bowl combine mayonnaise, dressing and mustard.
Mix well. Add cucumbers, tomatoes, green pepper, onions, salt and pepper. Also add chicken and macaroni
Toss to mix well.
Put in covered salad bowl and refrigerate.
Until well chilled.

title: meat loaf and gravy duet
directions: Mix ground beef and soup.
Mix thoroughly on large piece of aluminum foil, being carefully not to puncture foil.
Shape into loaf.
Pour soup across top of loaf.
Seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Press in pie plate with a spoon or by hand.
Prick bottom of crust with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix good.
Without stirring, cook until 300°.
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto cookie sheet with 1/2-inch layer of powdered sugar.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: gingersnap dip
directions: In a small bowl combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and spices.
Beat in
Cool Whip until blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Also good to dip apple wedges.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Add half the milk and 1/2 stick butter; mix together.
Pour half the cake mix in baking dish.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While it cools, melt caramels.
Add rest of milk to the melted caramels.
Pour over cake.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and unbaked cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still hot, lay Hershey bars on and spread.
Leave a day to let Hershey bars harden.

title: see's fudge
directions: In large pan, combine sugar, evaporated milk and pinch of salt.
Bring to a full boil for exactly 9 minutes.
Stir constantly.
In large mixing bowl, combine chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Add to cooked mixture when done.
Stir until well blended.
Put into 10 x 15-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak and onion in tablespoon of oil.
Stir in gravy mix, 1 1/4 cups water and soy sauce.
Stir until thickened.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add green peppers and tomato wedges. Simmer 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: nutty chocolate caramel bars
directions: Chop 4 squares chocolate; set aside.
Mix melted margarine with cookie crumbs.
Press into bottom of foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Top with caramel topping.
Pour milk into medium bowl; add pudding.
Beat with whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping, chopped chocolate and peanuts.
Spread over caramel topping.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Melt remaining chocolate with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Spread over pudding.
Chocolate hardens immediately.
Lift dessert from pan using "foil" hands.
Cut into bars.

title: spiced pot roast
directions: Brown beef; turn as needed.
Remove beef.
Add carrots, onions and celery.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add beef broth, stirring to loosen brown meat bits.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Return meat; cook until beef is tender.
Remove meat.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Return meat to pot.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add Jell-O and let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir well and chill overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping slightly. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: halloween cool whip graveyard treat
directions: Mix 2 cups of cookie crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and margarine; press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup sugar in bowl until smooth; stir in 1/2 of whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/2 cups; stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Spread remaining whipped topping over gelatin. Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Decorate as a graveyard. Makes 15 to 18 servings.
(Assorted rectangle shaped sandwich cookies, decorator icings and candy corn and pumpkins.)

title: spiced mocha drink
directions: Stir water, sugar, coffee, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in 4 cup measure.
Add chocolate.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in milk.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Beat with mixer until foamy.
Top each serving with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains 120 calories per serving.

title: raspberry beet jelly
directions: Bring to a hard boil the beet juice and Sure-Jell. Stir in sugar, jello and lemon juice. Bring to a boil and boil hard for 6 minutes; let stand a few minutes off heat. Skim and put into jelly jars. Can be sealed with wax.

title: monterey cheese log
directions: Beat together all ingredients until well blended.
Chill. Form into log and coat lightly with grated Parmesan cheese.
Wrap and chill.
Makes 1 (12 ounce) log, 1 1/2 cups.

title: moroccan chicken and couscous casserole
directions: Broil chicken, skin side up, to brown the skin and melt the fat.
Combine remaining ingredients in a casserole.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, on top.
Cover casserole with lid or foil.

title: swank porterhouse steak
directions: Slash fat edge of steak; don't cut into meat.
Slitting from fat side, cut pocket in each side of lean almost to the bone. Combine salt, garlic, pepper and celery salt.
Put in pocket in steak.
Mix Claret and soy sauce; brush on steak.
Grill over hot coals a total of 25 minutes or until done to your liking.
Turning once, brush occasionally with soy mixture.
Makes 4 delicious servings.

title: mozzarella and tomato salad
directions: Combine Mozzarella cheese, tomato and onion.
Add oil and vinegar to taste.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover sliced cukes, onions, garlic, green pepper and red pepper with cracked ice and mix well.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar, turmeric and celery seed.
Cook.
Boil good.
Put in jars and boil in water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted margarine and sugar.
Press into 8-inch pan.
Bake medium for few minutes.
Cool.

title: dick cavett bread
directions: Cut round hole in top of bread and remove (be careful to leave intact).
Scoop insides out of bread and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and spoon inside of hollowed bread.
Place top back on bread and double wrap with tinfoil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serve immediately.
Use Sociables crackers or bread crumbs for dipping.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Mix until mixture forms a ball.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spread in greased 13-inch by 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: newburg sauce
directions: Mix together over low heat; cooked shrimp, 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Set this aside.
Then mix together 1 tablespoon butter and flour; add 1/2 cup cream (or half and half).
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in 2 beaten egg yolks, sherry and brandy.
Add shrimp mixture and eat until your heart's content 'cuz it's good!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in egg.
Coat all sides with Progresso onion bread crumbs.
Place on a greased shallow baking pan, skin side up.
Dribble with oil.
Bake, uncovered, until chicken is browned and crisp, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix spices and brown Sugar Twin and salt together.
Toss apples with lemon juice, then mix in spice mixture.
Pour into pie crust and dot with margarine.
Place top crust on, vent with fork and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: spinach dunk
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.
Serve in sourdough bread.

title: hanukkah cookies(cookie dough: makes 32)
directions: In a mixing bowl or food processor, cream the butter and cream cheese together.
Beat in the flour, little by little.
Knead the dough lightly until all the flour is incorporated.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Divide the dough into 2 portions.

title: hobo stew
directions: Mix ground chuck with salt and pepper.
Press into an 8 x 10-inch pan in the bottom.
Cover with sliced potatoes, carrots and sliced onion.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: basic dessert crepes
directions: Combine all crepe ingredients in medium bowl and beat with rotary beater until combined and smooth.
Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet.
Spoon in 2 tablespoons batter; lift and tilt skillet to spread batter.
Brown on 1 side only.
(Or cook on an inverted crepe pan.)
Invert pan over paper toweling; remove crepe.
Repeat to make 16 to 18 crepes, greasing skillet occasionally.

title: blueberry refrigerator jam
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over grape juice concentrate in a saucepan. Let stand 1 minute.
Add blueberries and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly.
Cool.
Pour preserves into airtight containers and chill until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells in plenty of boiling, salted water for 12 to 15 minutes; drain.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and beaten eggs; blend with salt, pepper and parsley.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in a rectangular baking dish.
Place stuffed shells 1 deep in casserole; top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; cover with a sheet of aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well (add a few nuts in mixture).
Form into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll balls into 1 3/4 cup of chopped pecans until all covered.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: slush cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1 cup pecans thoroughly.
Pat in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven and cool.
Combine the cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix the instant pudding with milk; beat until ready.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip; top with ground pecans.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Serves 12.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla; beat for 5 minutes scraping from sides frequently.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into pie shell and chill. Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip and garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: blueberry french toast
directions: Cut bread into 1 inch cubes; place half in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cut the cream cheese into 1 inch cubes; place over bread.
Top with blueberries and remaining bread.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and syrup; mix well.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 25-30 minutes more or until golden brown and the center is set.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in onion, if wanted, and chicken; mix well. Place 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each roll. Fold edges of roll around filling. Brush tops with melted margarine and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: venison steak and gravy
directions: Coat steak with flour and brown in
hot oil.
Remove from pan and drain.
Return to pan and add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on consistency desired.

title: mary's barbecue brisket
directions: Mix spices and Worcestershire sauce into a paste.
Rub on both sides of meat.
Seal well in heavy foil and bake 8 hours or overnight at 225°.
Pour off liquid and cool, then refrigerate until cold.
Slice thin and return to pan. Add 2 cups sauce and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sombrero pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Add water and taco seasoning mix; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Drain and add water chestnuts and dill weed.
Marinate in dressing for 1 hour or more.
If desired, use chopped celery and green onion to taste.

title: "beau"nz (for your dog)
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cream butter and egg.
Add dry mix to water and creamed mix; knead.
Shape into knots, pretzels or cut with bone-shaped cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 1 dog.

title: almond cream strawberries
directions: Cut stems off berries.
Cut deep X in top of berries.
Gently spread apart to make petals; set aside.

title: easy pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in prepared muffin pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
May add pecans or raisins for variety.

title: sandy's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy with a lemon color. Add sugar and applesauce. Beat well. Stir in zucchini. Add in dry ingredients. Beat well. Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 5 small loaf pans.

title: raisin caramel pie
directions: Boil the raisins, sugar, water and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes in a 2-quart saucepan.
Beat egg yolks and add milk, cornstarch and cinnamon (mix cinnamon with cornstarch and dissolve in part of the milk first).
Add to the raisin mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: baked crabmeat-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Reserve caps.
Chop stems to make 1 cup.
Cook chopped stems and green onion in butter or margarine until just tender.
Stir in flour, savory and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; add wine and 2 tablespoons water. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in crabmeat and Parmesan.
Fill mushroom caps with crabmeat mixture.
Place mushrooms in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch looking pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Makes 24.
Enjoy!!

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together.
Combine the croutons, butter and water.
Put half of crouton mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over croutons.
Top with remaining crouton mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in broth until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until noodles are tender.
This is an easy recipe that is very good and rich.

title: tamale and chili dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in saucepan.
Add in 1/4 pound Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts and serve with Fritos.

title: beef and barley skillet supper
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until barley is cooked about 20 minutes and serve.

title: venison hobo(serves 4)
directions: In 4 pieces of aluminum foil, place all of the ingredients. Cover with foil so that everything is covered.
Place over open campfire and cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients and bring to boil.
Coat popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, then break apart.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer together for 5 minutes the juices, sugar, cloves and cinnamon; strain.
Make tea with tea bags according to directions on box; should be about 12 cups.
Let sit about 1 hour; combine with juice.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan and brown onions.
Add broth, garlic powder and salt; simmer.
Place soup in bowls with bread pieces and cover with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted and brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend until thickened. Pour into crust.

title: one-eyed monster
directions: Spread margarine on both sides of bread.
Cut a hole in the center with a biscuit cutter.
Brown one side of bread in pan over medium heat.
Turn add 1 egg into the hole and cook for 3 minutes. Cover and cook 3 more minutes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° until knife comes clean (approximately 50 minutes).

title: barbecue beef cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together eggs, barbecue sauce and ground beef.
Separate biscuits.
Press into bottom and sides of muffin pans.
Spoon beef mixture into each shell.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: creole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk until smooth.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner (microwave)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine water, bouillon, thyme, rosemary and bay leaves.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place breast side down in casserole.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 10 minutes in microwave.
Turn chicken over.
Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots around chicken and cook, covered, on 50% power (Medium) for 30 to 40 minutes, until drumsticks move easily in sockets and vegetables are tender.
Turn dish once during cooking.
Skim fat from pan juices and remove bay leaves.
Pour 1 cup pan juices into 4-cup glass dish.
Combine buttermilk and flour and stir into pan juices.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 3 to 4 minutes, uncovered, or until thick.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Spoon some gravy on chicken and vegetables and serve.
Save remaining gravy to pass at the table.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together and put into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: best cutout cookie receipt ever
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add cream.
Sift dry ingredients with flour and add.
Chill dough 4 hours or overnight. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: eggplant rolls
directions: Wash and peel eggplant; slice lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices. Soak for 10 minutes in salted water.
Pat dry with a paper towel. In a large skillet, greased or sprayed with Pam, braise slices until tender.
Drain on towels.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie filling) thoroughly.
Put 3/4 of dough in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the pie filling over the dough and top with the rest of the dough.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients by hand and set aside.
Sift the flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt together.
Add the mixed water, oil and vanilla to the sifted mixture.
Fill paper muffin cups 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.
Drop 1 heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mix in center.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer strawberry angel dessert
directions: Add boiling water to jello and sugar; stir until dissolved. Add strawberries, stir until thawed.
Place in refrigerator until syrupy; then stir in whipped cream.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with angel food cake, pour 1/2 the strawberry mixture over cake; then repeat layers again cake, then strawberries. Refrigerate until firm and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll into small ball and flatten with a fork on greased sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven.
(These do not use any flour.)

title: lemon surprise
directions: Mix well and pat out thin into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour over butter.
Pour can of fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Make your selection carefully.
Do not choose too young or green but mature and ripe, coming from good stock.
Do not keep in a stew or hot water or pickle.
This tends to make them sour, hard or bitter.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in ice cream freezer; freeze.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, garlic powder; salt and pepper. Cook and drain noodles.
Add to hamburger mixture and simmer.

title: chicken enchilada ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop chicken and olives.
Add cheese, green chilies, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Seed and chop 1 tomato. Slice lime in half.
Juice 1/2 of lime to measure 1 teaspoon. Reserve remaining lime for garnish.
Add chopped tomato and lime juice to chicken mixture.
Keep 2 tablespoons of chips and add remaining chips to chicken mixture.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining chips on large round baking stone.	Arrange crescent triangle in a circle with wide ends overlapping in center and points toward outside.
Scoop chicken mixture onto widest end of triangle.
Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide end. (Filling will not be completely covered.)
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Place first 2 cups cereal in bowl, add boiling water. Set aside to cool. In a large bowl cream together butter, sugar, and eggs. Add buttermilk and soaked bran mixture, beat well. Sift together flour, soda, and salt. Add dry ingredients to buttermilk mixture and stir until flour is mixed in. Stir in the additional 4 cups cereal. Store batter in tightly covered container in refrigerator, for up to 3-4 weeks.

title: coconut egg
directions: Start with oleo, and beat until creamy.
Add some sugar (1 pound), then syrup.
Add as much sugar as you can and 1/2 bag coconut.
When too stiff for mixer, add rest by hand.
Make take more or less sugar, depending on oleo.
Should be pliable and able to form an egg or bite-size pieces.
Put on pan and refrigerate until cool (even overnight).
Dip in chocolate and put on wax paper to cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini and stir. Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon to creamed mixture.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pretzel salad 1
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush pretzels in a square baking dish. Cut stick of butter into 5 or 6 pieces and lay on top of pretzels.
Sprinkle sugar over pretzels and butter.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Stir and press into crust.
Let cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Shred chicken breasts. Place in a bowl. Saute onion and green pepper in a tiny bit of oil. Add to chicken. Stir in both cans of soup. Add pimento. Place in 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with almonds, crushed potato chips and cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until thoroughly cooked.

title: cranberry orange jello salad
directions: Section oranges; then finely dice and drain.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Stir cranberry sauce until smooth and blend into gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in diced oranges and nuts.
Pour into 5 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 1/4 cups or 8 servings.
This salad is especially good served with chicken or turkey.

title: sweet 'n sour baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to
medium
skillet heat butter until melted.
Add onion,
green	pepper	and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Stir in ketchup, pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce, garlic salt, salt, pepper and ginger.
Cook, stirring constantly	until
mixture	boils.	Add
pineapple. Arrange chicken in	13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over. Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover;	bake
minutes longer or until done.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in slightly salted boiling water for 5 minutes, drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine macaroni and mushrooms with other ingredients.
Place in a 6 c. buttered casserole. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel apples
directions: In a heavy pan, over low heat, melt caramels with water.
Stir occasionally until smooth.
Wash and dry apples, remove stems and insert wooden sticks in stem end.
Dip apples in melted caramel; scrape excess from bottom.
Place on parchment paper or buttered waxed paper.
Chill to set.
Makes 10 old-fashioned delicious Christmas treats.
Use the crispest, juiciest apples you can find.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; mix ingredients and pour into buttered pudding dish.
Bake 3 hours in a very slow oven (250°).
Stir 3 times during the first hour of baking to prevent rice from settling.

title: make ahead guacamole
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Whisk in lemon juice, mashed avocado, mayonnaise and salt.
Stir in minced onion and tomato.
Turn into 3 cup mold or bowl.	Make in a.m. and serve in p.m. and it will not darken.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Soak brown rice for 2 hours.
In large casserole mix all ingredients (except almonds).
Lightly sprinkle almonds on top. Bake for 1 1/2 hours, covered at 350°.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add sour cream and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; add lemon or vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with tumbler dipped in flour.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain, mash and drain again. Combine other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil and fry 5 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let dough defrost until it can be worked.
While dough is defrosting (about 2 hours), brown meat with onions and bell pepper and preparing sausage as instructed.
Drain fat from meat mixture. Spread each bread loaf on separate well buttered sheets of foil; sprinkle meat mixture generously down middle of each loaf, followed by a layer of mushrooms and cheeses.
Fold sides of dough over top of the filling, making sure all mixture is covered completely.
Brush top with butter; fold foil around the loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Unwrap and bake until brown.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: *For the low-fat diet, substitute 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup oil.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and cut chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat broth and soup.
Bring it to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine; add pepper.
Mix other ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fig jam
directions: Pour boiling water over figs to cover; let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain, stem and chop figs.
Add sugar and 3/4 cup water. Slowly bring to a boil, stirring often until sugar dissolves. Cook rapidly until thick.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking. Add lemon juice and cook for 1 minute longer.
Pour hot jam into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Seal at once.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions in oil until well done.
Put in deep casserole dish.
Add peppers, barbecue sauce, tomatoes, pinto beans and sugar.
Mix corn bread mix as directed.
Spread evenly over ingredients.
Bake at 450° until brown and crusty, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pilot's grill cheese dip
directions: Use either cocktail frankfurters or cut inch-long pieces of regular frankfurters.
Simmer together with 1 (10 ounce) jar currant jelly, mixed with 2 tablespoons prepared mustard, until sauce thickens and hot dogs are piping hot.
Use toothpicks for serving, leaving dogs in sauce.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix banana, sugar, buttermilk, shortening, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add to ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beer batter chicken nuggets
directions: Mix beer, Bisquick and garlic powder in a bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in batter and deep fry to golden brown.

title: pasta sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain. In a greased casserole, combine sausage, sauce, pasta and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with Mozzarella cheese; heat until cheese melts. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: broccoli with oil and lemon vinegar
directions: Cook broccoli until tender-crisp.
Drain and put in serving dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli. Serve hot or cold.

title: chart house bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place in mixing bowl
the
sour
cream,
mustard, black pepper, salt, garlic
powder
and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend for 2 minutes at low speed.
Add mayonnaise.
Blend 1/2 minute at low speed, then blend
minutes at medium speed.
Crumble cheese by hand into very small
pieces
and add.
Blend at low speed no longer than 4
minutes.
Must
sit	24
hours
before using. Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Make a big 10-inch skillet or 2 small pans of cornbread.
Cook whole chicken and remove from broth.
Debone chicken.
Using broth, add 1/2 stick butter and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well. Break up cornbread; add onions, sage to taste, salt and pepper. Start adding broth and mash up fine.
I use the potato masher getting it smooth and tasting as you go.
Grease oblong dish or pan and pour in half of dressing and then add chicken and finish filling with dressing.
Pour a cup of broth on top and cook at 350° until done (about 1 hour).
Don't overcook.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix Krispies, margarine, sugar and peanut butter with hands until well mixed.
Form into balls.
In double boiler, melt chips and paraffin.
Dip balls with toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to harden.
Store in airtight container in cool place.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and quarter unpeeled apples into 4 to 6-quart pot or Dutch oven.
Cook until very soft.
(Can be cooked in crock-pot or slow cooker.)
Press through food mill.
Boil 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and spices.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil gently.
Stir frequently until desired thickness.
Carefully put hot butter into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: cathy's casserole
directions: Add spices and tomato sauce to meat.
Combine chopped onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles and place in large casserole dish.
Next add meat mixture.
Add cream cheese mixture. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Add grated onion and grated raw potatoes to pancake mix.
Bake on hot griddle slowly so that potatoes will cook done.
Serve with leftover roast and gravy.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix well.
This
pie crust can be mixed with an electric mixer.
It
will
keep
in
the
refrigerator for several days. This pie crust handles very easy and will make 2 or 3 crusts.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes.
Remove.
In an additional 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic powder until tender and liquid is evaporated.
Stir often.
Add soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return to skillet.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4.

title: my favorite potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Grease oblong baking dish.
Slice potatoes and layer in dish with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Repeat until all potatoes are used up.
Pour milk over.
Cover with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grandmother's molasses cookies
directions: Put baking soda in sour milk and mix.
Put molasses, sugar, lard and egg in large bowl; mix well.
Add flour, salt and ginger, then add cup of sour milk and mix well.
Roll out about 1/4 inch thick and bake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Chop shrimp and combine with other ingredients.
Chill and serve with scoop Fritos.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Place beef in foil lined pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix ketchup and Open Pit together and pour over meat.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 475°.
Lower temperature to 325° and cook for about 3 hours (depending on weight of meat).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir sugar and cocoa into margarine.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with fork.
Add milk; stir well.
Pour into pie shell and bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°
or until set.
For tarts, bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: trail snack
directions: Mix all together and eat.

title: gallon punch
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon container and fill up the rest of the container with water.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans until smooth.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 pies.
Can be frozen.
Delicious.

title: fajitas
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Cut into strips and beat until tender.
In a bowl mix all seasonings, worcestershire, and A1.
Add meat. Marinade for 1 hour or over night.
Puree onions and bell peppers in a blender.
Lay meat on a pan and cook at 350 till brown (approx. 30 min.).
Turn meat and add puree and brown until done (approx. 15 minutes).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Fry onion and zucchini with oregano, margarine and garlic powder.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add cheese.
Mix with zucchini mixture.
Place rolls into large pie pan overlapping to form crust.
Put zucchini mixture into raw roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: pinto dumplings
directions: Cook pintos until about half done; drain water off.
Put pintos in the mixture of cornmeal, flour and soda.
Mold into baseball size balls.
Put into a pot of boiling water.
Cook slowly for about 1/2 hour.
Remove from water.
Cut open; pour meat grease over them and salt to taste.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust and set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over 3/4 cup of the skim milk in a small saucepan.
Soften 1 minute, then heat and stir until gelatin completely dissolves. Place cottage cheese in a blender or food processor; blend until completely smooth.
Add gelatin mixture, remaining milk and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth, scraping down sides of blender occasionally.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Beat until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons granulated sugar slowly. Beat until stiff enough to form peaks.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix well.
Roll in log, then roll in chopped parsley. Refrigerate.

title: creamy chicken breasts(serves 8)
directions: Split chicken into 8 pieces and arrange in greased casserole. Place cheese slice on each chicken piece.
Mix soup and wine until smooth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until done.

title: georgia cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Cool; crumble into very small pieces.
Cook bacon; drain and crumble or chop.
In large glass bowl, layer half
of the cornbread; top with half of pickle relish, juice, tomatoes, pepper, onion, bacon and 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Repeat layers, reserving small amount of tomatoes and bacon for garnish.
Refrigerate; serve chilled. Yields 12 servings.

title: sweet and sour ground beef
directions: Brown beef slowly.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Pour over hot cooked beef.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, green pepper, onion tops and shredded carrots.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pork adobo(philippines)
directions: Place the pork in a saucepan.
Add vinegar, garlic, pepper, salt or soy sauce and water.
Cover the saucepan and cook slowly until the meat is tender and the broth is about 1/4 cup.
Drain the meat; separate the pieces of garlic from the pork and fry in lard until brown.
Add the pork and fry until brown also.
Add the broth and let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sumi salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil and Ramen flavor mix; stir until well blended. Don't add noodles, nuts and dressing until ready to serve.
You can substitute 1/2 balsamic vinegar and 1/2 wine vinegar for rice vinegar.
Cooked chopped chicken may be added.

title: melinda's coca cola cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and sugar in a bowl.
In a saucepan combine butter, cocoa and coke and bring to a boil.
Pour this over the mix of dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan.
Top with Coca Cola Cake Icing.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Heat Hershey bars and Eagle Brand milk over low heat until melted.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Turn out into a large buttered pan (glass is better) and let stand several hours.
Cut into squares and store loosely covered for a couple of days or more, if left at room temperature.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers and butter. Pour into baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in 1 1/2 cups water to which 3/4 teaspoon salt has been added, for about 10 minutes.
Drain and add next 4 ingredients and pepper to taste.
Butter a baking dish and put 1 cup stuffing in the bottom.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, cottage cheese and margarine.
Add onions and broccoli.
Add corn bread muffin mix and salt.
Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be frozen for later use.
Thaw, then warm.

title: slumgullion(a quick recipe that all the kids like, big and small)
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Add tomato soup (Campbell's or equivalent).
Season with salt and pepper.

title: onion potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into wedges or quarters.
Coat wedges with oil.
Put onion soup mix and potato wedges into a large Ziploc bag.
Shake well.
Lay wedges on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chipotle chicken salad tacos
directions: In a large bowl, mix vinegar, olive oil and chipotles. Season to taste with salt, about 1/4 teaspoon.
Add cabbage, carrot, onion, cilantro and chicken.
Toss and let stand 15 minutes.
Put into a wide, shallow serving bowl, dot with avocado and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with tortillas.
Makes about 4 cups, enough to fill 12 to 16 tacos and serve 4.

title: cake frosting
directions: In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, vanilla and egg whites.
Blend well.
Beat in remaining sugar until smooth and creamy.
Optionally, flavor with chocolate or strawberry, and frost cake.

title: kids' english muffin pizza
directions: Place muffins on a cookie sheet, cut side up.
Spoon sauce on cut side and add toppings and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Place chicken in roaster.
Add soups and water.
Cover; bake in oven for 2 hours at 350°.
Don't peek!

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 pints.

title: annie's chocolate syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: 15 minute soft steak tacos
directions: Heat skillet.
Add steak; cook until lightly browned; stir in water, salsa and seasoning mix.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon steak mixture evenly onto tortillas and top with Kraft shredded cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour mixture in an 8-inch pie pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: meredith's potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Lay hash browns to cover bottom of pan. Top each hash brown patty with a pad of butter and salt and pepper.
Repeat with second layer.
Pour milk 1/2 way up the pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Take out and stir and add more milk so that mixture is very moist.
Put back in oven for 30 minutes. Top with grated Parmesan cheese and put back in oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aubree's favorite "no bake" cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil and continue to boil for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in two large bowls.
Mix nuts with each bowl. In a 5-quart saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil and stir for five minutes.
Pour half of syrup over each bowl of popcorn and stir to coat.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses. Sift together and stir in, flour, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of large walnuts. Dip tops in sugar.
Place, sugared side up, 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with 2 or 3 drops of water to produce a crackled surface.
Bake just until set, but not hard at 375°, about 10 to 12 minutes.
(I never bake longer than 10 minutes, because we prefer a chewy cookie.)
Makes 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken or breasts.
Remove the bones and reserve the broth.
Do not salt.

title: lemon curd
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy pan and cook over lowest heat until mixture thickens enough to coat a spoon.
Do not let it boil.
Add lemon peel.
Refrigerate until ready to use as tart or jelly roll filling.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: lemon and garlic shrimp
directions: Peel and devein the shrimp.
Mince the garlic and chop the scallion.
Squeeze 2 tablespoons of juice from the lemon.
Heat the butter and oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add the shrimp, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt.
Saute, stirring, until the shrimp turns pink, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in the lemon juice and scallion.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 1 hour in regular size loaf pan.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook beef; drain off grease.
Add all ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix.
Pour batter into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch baking tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do the toothpick test to see when center is done.
Cool for 10 minutes and then remove from pans.

title: hot venison sandwich
directions: Place venison in a crock-pot (no need to cut up meat).
Mix in all other ingredients.
Set on low and cook all day.
Serve on good hearty rolls.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine chopped vegetables in medium bowl.
Thoroughly mix oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Add sauerkraut.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and add chicken wings.
Marinate overnight.
Bake on greased pan 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from sauce to serve, either hot or cold.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll thawed bread dough (using flour) to about 1/2-inch thick. Layer meat and cheese onto dough. Sprinkle with desired spices (garlic, Italian seasonings, etc.). Add any additional toppings (pepperoni, hot peppers, green peppers, onions, etc.). Roll each loaf and tuck ends inward. Be sure to pinch ends and seam to securely seal loaf. Brush each loaf with Italian salad dressing. Sprinkle with kosher (coarse) salt and poppy seeds. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate and butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan; you can use a Pyrex dish.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place butterscotch chips and 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk; set aside.
In medium microwave bowl, place chocolate chips, remaining sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; microwave on High (100%) for 1 minute.
Stir until chips are melted.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar and oil.
Then add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Then add nuts, coconut and zucchini.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Yields 2 large loaves or 5 small loaves.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg.
Add vanilla. Add remaining ingredients, flour and milk, alternating each one. Bake in a cold oven (do not preheat oven) at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Grease pan.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix in blender and refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.
Serve with ham, turkey, pork or lamb.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine in pan and cook until desired thickness. Add to unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in eggs.
Add melted butter and buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.
Pour in chilled pie shell.
Bake at 415° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with honey, mustard and curry powder. Skin chicken pieces and dip in mixture.
Place in foil-lined flat pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting several times.

title: baby bird seed
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve as a dry snack in a bowl or take along in a sandwich bag.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Bake, covered, for 6 hours at temperature no higher than 300°. Shred meat while hot and serve on buns.

title: james' spicy chili
directions: Put first five ingredients in a large skillet and cook over medium heat until meat and vegetables are cooked.
While meat mixture is cooking, put remaining ingredients in a large stew pot over low heat.
When meat mixture is done, add to tomato mixture and simmer over very low heat about 2 hours.

title: chocolate and peanut butter dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter into flour until mixture crumbles.
Stir in 2/3 cups chopped nuts.
Press evenly onto bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Fold in 4 1/2 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled flour layer.
Mix together chocolate and vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with peanuts or pecans.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: beef and oysters
directions: Coat sirloin with flour and brown in butter with onion.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until tender.
Just before serving, add oysters.
Serve over buttered rice.
Very good!

title: low calorie crab mornay
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Combine 1/2 cup skim milk and 1 teaspoon cornstarch and add to heated mixture.
Cook and stir constantly about 2 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup shredded Swiss cheese and 8 ounces cooked crabmeat (can use imitation crab).
Spoon into small individual dishes.
Sprinkle with paprika and broil for 2 minutes.
Or continue to cook on stove until heated throughout and serve over rice.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add broth and simmer 20 minutes.
Add potato soup and cheese.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve in soup buns.
Cut off top, scoop out inside.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Blend in sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in pecans and chips. Drop on shiny side of foil on cookie sheet.
Put cookies in oven and turn oven off and leave overnight.
If too sticky, leave out in air and dry.

title: indian style jerky
directions: Mix soy sauce, liquid smoke, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce in medium size bowl.
Cut meat in thin slices when half frozen.
Lay slices of meat in bowl until thawed.
Add mixture. Let stand for about 1 to 2 hours, longer for stronger taste.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using the smallest cupcake tins and petit fours
paper cups, sprinkle bottoms with crumbs.
Place eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream in blender; mix well.
Add cheese gradually while mixing.
Add margarine.
Pour petit fours cups approximately 3/4 full.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until set in center.
If cakes sink in center, don't worry.
Chill.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk as per directions.
Mix in all of whipped topping.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Pour half pudding mixture over crackers in pan and spread evenly.
Add second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour remainder of pudding over crackers and spread evenly.
Add one more layer of crackers.
Pour melted chocolate over crackers.
Chill in fridge for 2 hours before serving.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut all vegetables finely.
Place all ingredients in pan; simmer over low heat until soup thickens.
Add more water if needed.
Contains 97 calories per serving.

title: fresh fruit on a spit(fresh fruit with a different flavor)
directions: Peel and cut fruit into one inch cubes. String on 2 spits or on skewers ending each one with a berry. Place over medium coals 3-4 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve while warm.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Heat for 1 minute.
Add frozen potatoes.
Toss together, but do not overmix. Pour into well buttered steam table pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 60.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Put pretzels and oleo into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Cover with pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: You will also need no-stick cooking spray.

title: banana supreme
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high until light, about 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, softened butter and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes and spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: potato planks
directions: Wash potatoes; cut lengthwise into eighths. Set oven control to broil and/or 550°. Place potatoes, cut sides down, in ungreased jelly roll pan; brush with oil. Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle potatoes with half of the mixture. Broil potatoes with tops about 3 inches from heat until potatoes begin to bubble slightly, about 10 minutes.

Turn; brush with oil and sprinkle with remaining salt mixture. Broil until golden brown and tender, about 5 minutes longer. Serve with sour cream if desired. Makes 6 servings with 85 calories per serving.

title: strawberry-pineapple jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot (boiling) water.
Add crushed pineapple and bananas and mix well.
Put mixture into a 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Jell in refrigerator.
Spread sour cream on top.

title: breaded venison steaks
directions: In a glass baking dish, marinate the steaks in lemon juice for 1 hour.
Pat them dry with a paper towel and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dip in eggs, beaten with water, then dip in flour.
Shake off the excess and finally dip them in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients and spread on Italian bread. Spread on both sides of the slice.
Spread remaining butter on top of loaf and sprinkle with paprika and grated Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Put cooked, drained hamburger meat (half of it) in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, then put a layer of onion rings.
Add a layer of sliced potatoes, then pour creamed corn over mixture.
Add rest of hamburger meat, onion and potatoes.
Mix milk and soup and pour over casserole.
Top with cheese, if you wish.
Bake at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: tomato provencale quiche
directions: For an 8-inch baked shell.
Blend tomatoes and garlic into onions; cook, stirring, 10 minutes or until thick.
Add seasonings. Let cool until tepid.
Beat in eggs and parsley.
Spread anchovies in the shell.
Add the puree and cheese.
Place sliced tomato on top.
Drizzle on a little oil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cider cup cocktail
directions: Chill the cider, pineapple and orange juice either separately or after mixing. Pour into punch glasses and garnish each with sprig of mint.

title: super crabmeat
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter about 5 minutes.
Add and cook the onion until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Fold in crabmeat.
Make paste using flour and milk.
Add to crab mixture and cook over low heat until it thickens.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into individual shells.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss pasta, salmon, tomatoes, cucumber and onion.

title: saft
directions: Mix all the juices with 4 quarts of water and stir well.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Mix broth, soup, butter, rice, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: olive crostini
directions: Chop olives coarsely in food processor.
Transfer to medium bowl.
With machine running, drop garlic through feed tube and mince.
Add Parmesan, butter and olive oil.
Process to a paste. Add butter mixture to bowl with olives.
Fold in Monterey Jack and parsley.
Mix well.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 3 long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper. Chill and slice.

title: seasoned chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken thoroughly.
Crush croutons in a flat dish.
Roll chicken in beaten egg, then roll in croutons and place in baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger and cabbage
directions: Brown in heavy skillet the ground beef and onions; drain off fat. Add shredded cabbage, chopped pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Cover and simmer until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cut center out of pumpernickel bread.
Stir in mix.
Cut up remaining top part of bread in small pieces and use for dipping.

title: amanda's world barbecue sauce
directions: If you like it hot, add 2 tablespoons hot sauce.

title: raspberry whipped topping cappuccino
directions: Pour water into coffee maker. (May use full pot of water for weaker flavor. I prefer this.)
Place frozen topping into empty coffee pot. Brew coffee.

title: sweet chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt. Add just enough milk to make a paste; mix well. Add yolks; beat and mix well. Add the remaining milk and water. Cook over medium-low heat; stir constantly until thickened to prevent lumping and burning. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pie crust shell and spread evenly. Top with meringue; lightly brown. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and salt.
While still hot add cranberries (ground) and orange (squeeze juice into gelatin, grind the rind).
Cool.
Add celery and apples, cut fine and walnuts, cut up.
Put in 18 individual molds, a ring mold or bread pan.
If using individual mold, package each 2 in a pliofilm bag or heat-seal in cellophane.
Store up to 1 month only.

title: meat wrap
directions: Place tortilla flat on surface and spread cream cheese over top.
Place a piece of ham in center and roll into a wrap and place toothpicks in center to hold in place.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Pour chilled punch into punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and spoon sherbet into punch.
Add 1/2 sherbet at a time.

title: beef brisket marinade
directions: Rub into meat.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, turning once. Rinse off meat and coat with favorite barbecue sauce.
Bake covered with fat side up 6 hours at 275°.

title: nancy's taco salad
directions: Set the fritos aside for later.

title: prune bread
directions: Add salt and cinnamon to flour, then mix in order given, adding dry ingredients with buttermilk and soda mixture.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured pans or 4 small ones.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1/2 hour at 350° and 1/2 hour at 325°, or in small pans for 25 minutes at 350° and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs (one at a time) and pumpkin. Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to pumpkin mixture. Add water and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Add nuts and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine following and pour over veggies:
sugar, salad dressing, mustard, oil, vinegar and salt and pepper.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and oregano mixture.
Mix together lemon juice, garlic and olive oil.
Pour on chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Quartered onions and potatoes can be also baked with chicken.

title: tomatoes eisenhower
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Drizzle with brown sugar and 1 teaspoon onion.
Top the onion with a pinch of curry powder.
Finish with grated cheese.
Place in the oven or under broiler until bubbly.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Combine 1 egg and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in raisins. Knead on a floured surface for 1 minute.
Shape into a round loaf; place on a greased baking sheet.
Cut a 1/4-inch deep cross in top of loaf.
Beat remaining egg; brush
over loaf.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Add corn, peas, onion and potatoes in large pot.
Add chicken, tomato juice and hot pepper.
Add broth from boiled chicken.
Let boil for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Let simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: tom's fried catfish
directions: Fill the kitchen sink with cool water; add about 2 to 3 tablespoons salt and swish around.
Place catfish in water for approximately 30 minutes.
Remove fish from water, rinse and place in large bowl of milk.
Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge catfish with mixture, shaking off excess.
Fill deep skillet half full with canola oil.
Heat to 350°.
Add catfish in a single layer and fry until golden brown, 5 to 6 minutes, depending on size.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in a fondue pot or crock-pot.
Use wooden meat skewers or forks to dip the bread into the cheese.
Eat one piece of cheese covered bread at a time, just after it is dipped in the cheese.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat
egg
yolks
well.
Add
sugar
and flour to eggs; beat until
smooth.
Add
hot
milk,
stirring.	Add vanilla. Bake in pie shell about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When firm, top
with meringue
made
of egg whites, adding 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg white and brown in oven.

title: nanny's pepper jelly
directions: Blend cut up peppers in blender until liquified.
Mix sugar, water and peppers in large pot.
Boil fast for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo and food coloring.

title: easy as 1-2-3 peach cobbler
directions: Drain syrup from peaches into a bowl and set aside.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place sliced peaches to cover bottom.
Sprinkle entire box of cake mix over peaches.
Pour peach syrup over cake mix.
Cut half stick of butter or margarine into small "pats" and place on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (or until golden brown).

title: parish patch sawdust pie
directions: Combine coconut, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar.
Mix in egg whites.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes in crock-pot
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (thin).
Put in crock-pot with 1/4 cup cheese, onion, ham and milk.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 hours.
Add cheese the last hour of cooking time.

title: mac & cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make very soupy.
Cover with tin foil. Bake in 350 degree oven for 35-40 minutes.
If too much liquid, remove foil and bake until liquid is absorbed.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in molasses, beaten with eggs. Re-sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition until blended.
Bake in a greased 9-inch tube pan in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
This is delicious with apple butter as icing while cake is still warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Gradually add water to sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add dry jello to mixture and stir until dissolved.
Fold into strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Chill.

title: fabulous pecan bars
directions: Toast chopped pecans in 350°
oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Melt butter, peanut butter and butterscotch chips together over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows, pecans and 3/4 cup coconut.
Mix well.
Pat mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on remaining coconut.
Cool until firm in refrigerator. Cut into small bars.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Slice 1 1/2 of the bananas.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Pour pudding over bananas.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over pie.
Garnish with remaining banana, sliced and dipped in lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Serves 8.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring carrots with water to cover to a boil for 5 minutes. Drain and cool.
In a medium bowl, add salt, pepper and mustard. Beat in a little of the oil to blend with mustard.
Add balance of oil, sugar, vinegar and soup. Beat to blend.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: miracle soup
directions: This soup was "invented" in 5 minutes on a day when soup did not "show up."
Serves 10.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix altogether.
Make into meatballs and fry in skillet. After browning, turn low for about 30 minutes.

title: scramble(this is almost like popcorn...you can't stop eating it)
directions: Pour pretzels, dry cereal and nuts in a large roaster.
Heat butter, sauce and salts over low heat and pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Drain on paper toweling until cool.
Store in tins.
This will keep indefinitely.

title: potato fried cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll out with rolling pin. Cut out with donut cutter.
Heat a whole can of shortening on stove to form grease.
Bring grease to a boil.
Put donuts in grease until they turn a golden brown.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Brown beef with salt.
Drain.
Add broth, celery, onion, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
When tender, add tomato sauce, soup, corn and peas.

title: mexican cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together with a spoon.
Add 1 cup chopped
pecans.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate bottom mini cupcakes
directions: For Topping:
Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar, and salt until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.

title: garlic pita bread(kids)
directions: Cut pita bread in half.
Cut it open.
Butter bread.
Sprinkle with garlic bread spread or chopped garlic and garlic salt.
Broil in toaster oven.

title: jello-no bake mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press onto bottoms of each 12 Reynolds paper bake cups with a spoon or glass.
Beat milk and filling mix on low until blended.
Beat on medium for 3 minutes, filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumb mixture in bake cups.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with fruit, nuts or chocolate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix shortening, sugar and peanut butter until creamy.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Roll dough into balls about the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a crisscross design on each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Have a pocket cut in each chop along the fat side. Salt and pepper inside pockets. Toss together bread cubes, apple, cheese and raisins. Combine melted butter, orange juice, salt and cinnamon. Pour over bread fruit mixture and mix gently. Stuff pork chops lightly. Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Cover lightly with foil. Bake 15 minutes more. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, and water to 238° on candy thermometer. Add raw peanuts.
Cook to 290°, stirring all the time after adding nuts.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt, soda, and stir.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Can use raw cashews or pecans in place of peanuts.

title: cauliflower and pasta soup
directions: In a large pot, brown garlic in a little amount of olive oil. Add chopped tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Clean cauliflower and cut into florets.
Add to pot. Add enough boiling water to cover cauliflower and let cook 15 minutes.
If necessary, add more boiling water to pot and add pasta.
Cook until pasta is done.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and enjoy.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Put small amount of oil on griddle.
Put several spoonfuls on griddle for each pancake. Brown on both sides.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, onion, sour cream, butter, sour cream, salt and pepper.
After blending thoroughly, add cheese and hash browns. Mix and bake in uncovered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soup to go
directions: Brown hamburger meat in soup pot with minced onions.
Add 1 quart hot water and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and tomato paste and return to boil.
Ready to serve in 15 minutes.
Serve with corn bread and green salad.

title: stir and bake fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Put raisins in hot water and set aside.
Cut up all fruit.
Put all cut up fruit and whole nuts into large pan.
Drain raisins and add.
Add flour over fruit.
Stir with hands.
Add butter mixture and stir well (use hands).
I use a large roaster to mix and cook in.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.
Remove from oven.
Pack into tube or loaf pans greased with wax paper on bottom.
Let stand overnight. Return to warm oven for 5 minutes; empty.
Serves large crowd.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces.
Put in bottom of large saucepan.
Pour raw cabbage in, which has been added and shredded.
Add raw potatoes, cut in quarters.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and retain liquid.
Place potatoes, onion and bacon in saucepan.
Nearly cover with clam liquid and water. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, approximately 25 minutes.

title: apple or peach pie
directions: Mix flour, milk and sugar together.
Pour peaches or apples on top of butter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Chop bacon and mix lightly with meat, onion, green pepper, parsley and seasonings.
Shape into cakes and place them 3 inches under broiler heat.
Broil 12 minutes, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, sour cream, onions, half the chilies and 1 teaspoon bouillon.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, remaining chilies, green pepper, remaining bouillon, chili powder, sugar and cumin.
Simmer 10 minutes or until bouillon dissolves.
Soften tortillas according to package directions; fill each with equal portions of meat mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange in greased 3-quart shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Spoon tomato sauce over.
Cover; bake 20 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with additional sour cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sesame stuffing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a nonstick skillet.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Transfer vegetables to a mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Salt is optional.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together and add to first mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake in 400°oven for 8 to 12 minutes for chewy (barely browned), longer for crisp cookie.

title: chocolate cream dream supreme
directions: Put together flour, chopped pecans and melted butter in baking dish and bake 15 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix and put on top of the crust.
Put remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip and decorate with chocolate shavings or nuts.

title: chicken dish
directions: Make a cream sauce of the butter, flour, milk and 3 cups of the broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut mushrooms with chicken.
Add remaining cup of broth.
Put layer of rice in greased baking dish.
Add layer of chicken, layer of almonds and pimientos and cover with sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 16.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a layer each of graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate bits and nuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Makes 16 squares.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add salt; stir to dissolve.
Add flour.
Heat until mixture is bubbly.
Add milk; cook until near boiling and mixture thickens.
Add cheese and Tabasco.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save 2 tablespoons of juice.
Mix with other fruits, adding apples and bananas just before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and flour. Mix in pecans, dates and candied fruit. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, powder, salt and soda.
Combine the juice and rind of 1 orange and the shortening with enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Mix with the dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberries (chopped nuts and halved cranberries).

title: franklin nut cake recipe
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding a little flour and one egg at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan (use brown paper in bottom).
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Cool potatoes and then peel and dice.
Let eggs cool, then peel and chop.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with egg slices and paprika.

title: 24 hour omelette
directions: Place bread cubes in greased pan.
Pour other ingredients in topping with egg mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and brown about 5 minutes.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain peas, beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: quick gravy for rice or bread
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the flour and mix into a paste.
Add the hot water, stirring slowly.
Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until thick.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check at 50 minutes.
Cake will be moist.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and seed peppers.
Grind with onions.
Scald with hot water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Scald again.
Drain.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Cook 15 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: macaroon creams
directions: Melt almond bark in milk over boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Add coconut and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese bars
directions: Unroll 1 package rolls into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 1 egg yolk and 1 teaspoon vanilla together.
Spread over crust.
Cover filling with the other package of unrolled crescent rolls.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Spread over crust and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend flour and cinnamon and stir into butter mixture.
Pat into pan.
Beat water and egg white until frothy.
Brush over dough; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut immediately into finger-like strips (around 3 x 1-inch).
Great served with ice cream desserts.

title: your choice cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with blueberry, cherry or strawberry pie filling (your choice).
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Heat olive oil and saute the next 5 ingredients for about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and parsley and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan to serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Fold in pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350°F. for 60 to 65 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
When completely cooled, dust with confectioners' sugar.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients with mixer.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook beef until browned and drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients and 5 cups water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and remove bay leaf.

title: cheese dip mold
directions: Heat soup, cream cheese and gelatin.
Cool, then add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add whatever else you want (celery, onion, etc.).
Mix well and pour into mold.
Chill about 4 hours or overnight.

title: scalloped potato supreme
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, green peppers and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over potato mixture; cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molasses spice cookies(no fat)
directions: Mix together the Wonder Slim, sugar, water and molasses.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Mix all together, form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mozart mozzarella
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Mix with tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cheeses over top.
Lay out individual crescent rolls and spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Roll up and place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until crescent rolls are brown and done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: texas trash
directions: Layer cereals, pretzels and nuts in large roaster pan.
Pour and stir melted seasonings and grease into dry cereals.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes or will burn.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together as they are without adding any liquids.
Place in sealed container and shake well.
Store in dry place, shaking occasionally to keep well mixed.
