To serve, combine 2 to 2 1/2 teaspoons dry powder mix with 1 cup hot water.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cheese and condensed milk and beat until well blended (approximately 5 minutes) at medium speed with electric mixer. Add juice, vanilla and milk until thick and creamy smooth.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour until chilled.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread dough on jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Preheat oven according to package.
Cool.
Blend the mayonnaise, dry Hidden Valley mix and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled crust. Sprinkle your choice of vegetables over cheese mixture (all vegetables shredded).
May top with cheese.
Chill.
Cut and serve.

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix chopped cucumbers with salt and 4 cups water.
Let stand until you get onions and peppers cut up.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and boil 20 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: hawaiian rib eye
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Soak steaks in this marinade for at least 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Drain.
Broil steaks over a very hot grill.
The marinade can be used again and is great for chicken.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add red hots and dissolve.
Cool to lukewarm and add applesauce and lemon juice.
Pour half into mold and chill.
Beat cheese.
Add mayonnaise and nuts.
Spread over jello.
Top with remaining jello

title: do ahead sausage souffle
directions: Spread bread evenly in bottom of well-greased 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Arrange sausage on top.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Mix together mustard and soup.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk; mix well.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven to 300°.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until puffy and brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside and add lemon juice.
Combine Bisquick, 1/4 cup water (or milk), sugar and margarine.
Stir to a soft dough. Place blueberry mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, then drop dough by spoon on top of berries.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is light brown.
Serve warm.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare cake batter according to package directions, using eggs, water and oil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Spoon half of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chocolate chips over batter.
Gently spread remaining batter over top.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup chocolate chips and nuts over batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: red hot cinnamon candy
directions: Mix sugar, water, and syrup in heavy pan.
Turn on the vent over stove; open window if possible.
The fumes are quite strong. Boil until hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add oil and coloring.
Stir well; pour into cookie sheet which has been dusted with powdered sugar.
Cool; break into small pieces.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla in a third bowl.
Combine the egg and flour mixtures; add blueberries.
Alternate batter and sugar mixture in Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off the fat.
Add green pepper, celery, tomato soup or the tomato sauce.
Cook noodles according to package direction and add to hamburger mixture.
Add in rest of ingredients.
Simmer for a little while.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Mix with butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, leave enough to sprinkle the top with.
Put pineapple in 2-quart kettle, let come to a boil, then put in lemon Jell-O and let cool.
Let canned milk chill in fridge all night.
Put cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in bowl and mix together real good.
Then whip 2 cans of cooled milk with electric mixer until it whips up.
Put Jell-O, pineapple, cream cheese and sugar in and whip all up real well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with extra cracker crumbs.
Let chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together and pat firmly into a square baking pan (for a crust) the graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and oleo. Blend the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over the crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool until it is cold.

title: chile
directions: Cook onion and garlic in Crisco oil until limp; add ground beef and brown. Add all ingredients, except macaroni and beans. Simmer for 40 minutes. Prepare macaroni as per instructions. Add macaroni and beans; simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix together soup mix, mushroom soup, mustard, onions, salt, pepper, egg and sage.
Add bread crumbs and let set 10 minutes. Add meat and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: perfectly rich custard pie
directions: Scald milk and butter.
Let cool.
Add to egg mixture, composed of eggs, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Place in 450° preheated oven.
Bake 20 minutes only. Turn heat completely off.
Let pie stand in oven for 1 hour.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.

Mix together soup, milk and cheese, reserving 1/2 cup of the cheese. Combine cooked macaroni and soup mixture in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; knead until hand able; roll into walnut sized balls, (rounded teaspoon). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cool.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Heat peas.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in bowl or 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer the next 6 ingredients in order given.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top of layered salad.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Serves 10.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until just moist. Roll out thick and cut with round cutter.
Bake at 450 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: susie's supper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve chilled.

title: white rice
directions: Place the rice in salad oil to which you have added the garlic clove and the onion halves.
Slowly brown over low heat, stirring occasionally.
When rice is wheat colored, pour off most of the oil (leave about 1 tablespoon) and remove garlic.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook puddings and jello as instructed. Combine all three together and boil 1 more minute. Let cool. Fold in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill for two hrs.

title: mozzarella pork chops and spaghetti
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add chops and brown on both sides. Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Mix onion into fat in skillet and cook until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Mix in tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix, water and grated Parmesan-Romano cheese. Return chops to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender (45 to 55 minutes).
Baste occasionally while cooking. You may want to stir in small amounts of water.
Cook spaghetti or rice (amount you want).
Place in bottom of casserole.
Arrange pork chops on top and pour sauce over.
Top with Mozzarella.
Set under broiler to melt cheese.

title: hot squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, pepper and onion until tender; drain and mash. Add cheese and tomatoes.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle broken tortilla chips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: vegetable cheese squares (cold pizza)
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls and gently pat into a cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Heat cheese to lukewarm.
Combine all ingredients except flour; mix well.
Add flour until dough is stiff.
Let rise in a warm place 1 hour until double in bulk. Shape into a round ball and place in a greased loaf pan or 2-quart casserole.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Crust should be real brown; brush with butter.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Then add into all of the ingredients and bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple, its juice and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in jello and cream cheese. Cool.
Fold in nuts, celery, apples and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9-inch square dish.
Chill until set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook rice and shells; drain shells. Mix meat, rice and spaghetti sauce (1/2 jar).
Stuff the shells with meat mixture and cheese.
Place in lasagna baking dish. When all the shells are stuffed, pour remaining spaghetti sauce over shells, spreading it out.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomatoes and basil
directions: Slice tomatoes into a shallow dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over tomatoes.

title: berry-apple fantasy pie
directions: Prepare pastry and divide in half. On lightly floured surface, roll dough into 12-inch circle. Transfer the rolled out pastry onto 9-inch pie pan. In large mixing bowl, stir together the sugar, tapioca and cinnamon. Add the blackberries and apple slices. Toss gently and let stand 15 minutes. Spoon filling into pastry-lined pie pan. Dot with butter. Trim pastry even with edge of pie plate. Moisten the edge with water. On lightly floured surface, roll out remaining pastry into 12-inch circle. Cut slits in pastry to let steam escape. Place pastry on the filling. Trim the top crust. Fold the pastry and crimp edge. Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Slice pork to rind (not all the way through).
Freshen pork by boiling to get out salt.
May have to be done twice.
Add fresh water and cook until tender.
Save liquid to add to beans.
Cook beans in large pan with baking soda.
Bring to boil.
Pour off water and add fresh water.
Cook until skins start to fall off. Place in casserole.
Add liquid from pork.
Place pork on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are brown. Add more water while cooking so beans do not dry out, then enjoy!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Pour in water and baking soda, alternately adding flour and sour cream.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a 325° oven in Bundt pan for one hour.
Test for doneness.
Bake 15 minutes longer, if needed.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Mix the marmalade, lemon juice, oil, ginger, garlic powder and dried mustard.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly coat the chicken with the ingredients which have been mixed together.
Put chicken in a shallow baking dish (no cover) which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake until done, about 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 depending on size of chicken.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender, drain.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble. Brown chopped onion in bacon grease, drain.
Mix beans, bacon and onion, Cheddar cheese soup and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Crumble cracker crumbs and soak in oil.
Put cracker crumbs on top after you have put mixture in casserole dish.
Cook in oven for 25 minutes or until it bubbles at 325°.

title: rice dressing for duck
directions: Combine bacon drippings with flour in a skillet and brown slowly to make a roux.
Stir in giblets, onions, celery, pepper, garlic and seasonings.
Add hot water and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook as directed.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Chop vegetables and add to spaghetti.
Add salad seasoning and dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight. Toss before serving (more dressing may be added).

title: best ever peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add marshmallow cream.
Beat until well blended.
Add nuts if you wish.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix flour and cake mix together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; add flour.
Alternate with lemon juice and flavor.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped eggs and bacon(great for breakfasts, lunches, dinners or brunches!)
directions: Cheese Sauce:
Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring continually until thick.
Add cheese to above mixture.
After cheese has melted, add canned soup and heat well, allowing to simmer.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use cookie press.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Melt butter.
Set aside 1/2 cup of crushed Oreos.
Combine remaining Oreos with melted butter.
Press this mixture along bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan for layer one.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
(Save remaining 1/4 of Cool Whip for later.)
Spread this mixture for layer two. Mix together pudding mix and milk with mixer until stiff.
Spread for layer 3. Spread remainder of Cool Whip for layer 4. Top with remainder of Oreo crumbs for layer 5. Refrigerate; better if chilled overnight.

title: lemon bars
directions: Fork together 2 c. flour, powdered sugar, and butter. Pat to bottom of 9x 13 in. pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix well eggs, 2 c. sugar, and lemon juice.
Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour over crust. Bake 25 min.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: white chili
directions: In Dutch oven combine beans, chicken broth, garlic, chilies, oregano, cumin, red pepper, m.s.g., salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in chicken and simmer uncovered for 1/2 hour.
Before serving, stir in cheese until melted.
Great served with cornbread.

title: tortilla eggs
directions: Beat egg with water in a small bowl.
Lightly coat small skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat.
Pour in egg mixture; stir as egg begins to set.
Cook until set, but still moist.
Divide egg between tortillas; top with salsa and cheese and fold.
Makes 1 serving.

title: fern thomas' sugared nuts
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients to a very soft ball stage.
Stir in nuts.
Turn out onto waxed paper-covered tray and separate nuts. Cool.

title: cucumber yogurt spread
directions: Place cucumber in colander; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Let stand 10 minutes.
Rinse with cold water, drain on paper towels.
Place cucumber in blender or food processor and blend on high speed until pureed, about 2 minutes.
Place puree in colander.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as on package.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Melt butter, Pet milk and caramels in pan.
Pour over cake while hot.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over the mixture that has been baking.
Pour remainder of cake batter on top of the mixture of butter, chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake for 20 minutes more at 350°.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
(Good with white or chocolate icing.)

title: salmon fritters
directions: Remove the skin and bones from the salmon. Add the water and salt and pepper to taste. Add enough flour sifted with the baking powder to make a batter of the proper consistency.
Fry in hot lard or oil.
These fritters are improved by the addition of 1 well beaten egg in which case a little less water is used.

title: baked enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook meat and onion together.
Combine soups, milk, picante and 1/2 of cheese.
Prepare large casserole pan.
Begin layering the pan with tortillas, then meat mixture, then sauce mix.
Repeat until you have 2 or 3 layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: orange muffins
directions: In blender or food processor combine oranges, juice, oil and eggs until blended.
In another bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add the orange mixture to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in the raisins and nuts.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: green lima bean soup
directions: In a large pot, put first seven ingredients and bring to a boil. Then simmer for at least 2 hours.
Add the sweet corn, salt and pepper if needed.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Mix flour, soda and salt. Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco. Beat until fluffy. Add egg yolks, beating well. Alternate flour mixture and milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Add vanilla and mix well. Fold in coconut, pecans and beaten egg whites. Pour into 3 greased cake pans. (Baker's Secret is fantastic for baking cakes!)

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots in salt water.
Drain well.
Blend carrots and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: nutcracker sweet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Cream Crisco and peanut butter in large bowl at medium speed mixer. Blend in brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl and set aside.
Combine milk and vanilla in measuring cup.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix at low speed.
Scrape sides of bowl frequently.
Beat until blended. Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandma's corn casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Turn into greased 11 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. In large bowl with mixing spoon beat eggs, oil and sugar until smooth.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan on middle rack in oven for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Pour into margarine (do not stir).
Pour in can of peaches (do not drain, do not stir).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top (optional). Bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Other fruits may be used.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Roll chicken, add salt and pepper to taste.
In skillet, saute mushrooms, pepper, onions and pimentos in the butter.
After chicken is done, put macaroni in same chicken broth.
Save 1 cup broth.
Mix all ingredients and bake in oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: favorite doughnuts
directions: *To make sour milk, add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar or lemon juice to sweet milk.

title: peche melba* * * * *
directions: Cut peaches in half; remove seeds.
Combine syrup and vanilla; boil 5 minutes.
Poach peaches in syrup 10 minutes or until just tender; remove from syrup.
Chill peaches thoroughly.
Place scoops of ice cream in sherbet dishes; place peach halves over ice cream, cut side down.
Top with Melba Sauce.
Garnish with whole raspberries, if desired.

title: betty's cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
(Cover with water in blender.) Drain.
Add sugar; let set overnight or 6 hours.
Drain pineapple and cranberries.
Fold in Cool Whip no more than 2 hours before serving.
Freezable!

title: crunchy garden cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, cauliflower, peas, soup, water chestnuts, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 can onion rings and rest of ingredients except vegetables.
Add to vegetables.
Put remaining onion rings and extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy coney sauce
directions: Brown together the ground beef and chopped onion.
Add and simmer for several minutes the mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, vinegar, ketchup and salt (as needed).

title: escalloped ham and asparagus
directions: Layer potatoes, ham and asparagus in casserole dish.
Combine milk, flour and seasonings.
Mix until flour dissolves.
Pour evenly over casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade cookie mix
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix in sugars.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Blend in oats, mixing thoroughly.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
Makes 13 cups.

title: mexican tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas (flat not round).
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Cut each flat log into small bite size pieces and insert toothpick. Serve with picante sauce.

title: wild duck and turnips
directions: Soak the
wild	duck
one
day	in
water
containing a handful of	soda.
Drain
and
wash.
Soak	again overnight in water with	one cup vinegar.
Drain and wash.
Put 1/4 cup oil in a large
Dutch oven and brown duck all over.
Chop 2 onions and plenty
of	cubed
turnips and cover all with water.
Cook until all is stewed down.
Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add oil and bananas.
Mix in flour and nuts, but do not beat.
Pour in greased and floured or Pam sprayed loaf pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
This also makes nice muffins.
Great for Christmas gifts or any time of year.

title: praline sauce
directions: Combine sugar, half and half, and margarine in sauce pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat; stirring occasionally. Boil for 2 minutes, still stirring. Remove from heat add vanilla and almonds. Yields 1 cup.

title: homemade chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in microwave.
Mix sugar and cocoa, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes (ovens vary).

title: spiced fruit butter
directions: Peel and core or pit fruit; slice.
In a Dutch oven, combine prepared fruit, fruit juice and spices.
Bring to boiling; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until fruit is very tender.
Cool slightly.
Puree, part at a time, in a blender or food processor or with a food mill.
Return to Dutch oven.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat until desired consistency, stirring frequently. (This will take 10 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.) Remove from heat; stir in Equal.
Transfer to freezer containers or jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Store up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator or up to 3 months in the freezer.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Mix in last 3 ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: a.1. savory stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown meat and cook onion until done.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper; set aside.

title: low calorie apple cider salad
directions: Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup apple cider in a small, heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in remaining apple cider and lemon juice.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in apple and celery.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix and bring to a boil over medium heat (about 10 minutes) the sugar, water, syrup and food coloring.
Add peanuts; stir often until it reaches a medium hard ball stage or 250°.
Remove from heat and add oleo and salt.
Beat until it loses its gloss. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: homemade butter(eatable)
directions: Place heavy cream in a jar.
Secure lid.
Shake vigorously until cream thickens into butter.
Remove excess liquid.
Serve on crackers, bread or muffins.
May add salt to taste.

title: german apple coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in milk and lemon extract. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in bottom on well-greased 2-quart baking pan.
Arrange apple slices on top. Cut butter into the last 4 ingredients, sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° until it tests done with wooden toothpick (about 40 to 45 minutes).

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider and brown sugar.
Wrap spices in cheesecloth and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hot halibut dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and bake in a 9 x 9 dish for 45 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in milk.
Beat eggs well with sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add to cooked rice.
Stir until thickened (takes 1/2 hour).

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add water, vanilla, flour and pecans; mix.
Form into small crescents and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine everything but almonds.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Combine rice, water, pineapple syrup and salt.
Mix just to moisten rice.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, banana and lemon juice. Cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberries with orange juice
directions: Place strawberries in a large bowl, reserving several for garnish; set aside.
Rub sugar cubes over rind of oranges until soaked with oil.
Crush cubes with wooden spoon in a small bowl. Add juice of oranges; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over strawberries.
Cover and chill 2 or 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with whipped cream, reserved strawberries and mint leaves. Yield: 8 servings.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: Add boiling water, chopped celery, chopped nuts and grated Cheddar cheese and let set.
Whip Dream Whip, fold in Miracle Whip.
Spread on top of salad after it is set and garnish with grated cheese.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix together in salad bowl.

title: popcorn salad
directions: Dice all ingredients and toss them together.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter until smooth.
At low speed, add sugar gradually and beat in well.
Clean beaters.
Blend in honey at low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium-high speed after each addition.

title: cajun corn
directions: Bring salted water to boil; slowly stir in grits.
Cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed.
Add butter, garlic and spices.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil; add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer and simmer until medium thick.
Add raw meatballs and finish cooking until desired thickness, stirring often as not to burn.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Cook sugar and water slowly for 10 minutes.
Add grated rind to syrup and continue cooking 4 minutes.
Strain.
Add syrup to fruit juices.
Cool; pour into tray and allow to freeze firm. Remove mixture to ice cold mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until light.
Add cream and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which salt has been added.
Freeze.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter a deep baking dish.
Thinly slice onion and potatoes. Mix seasonings and flour into dish.
Add oleo and enough milk to reach edge of potatoes.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Puncture a few holes in plastic.
Cook on high for 12 minutes.
Remove and stir. Replace and remove as many times as necessary until potatoes are tender.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water and cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla, adding alternately.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add with butter and milk.
Don't overheat.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and add flour.
Then add broth and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add onions, almonds, salt and pepper.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in nuts, then flour and sugar.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Shape into small inch-size balls and roll in palm flat to crescent shape.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar twice.

title: honey-wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Whisk egg yolks with honey for 5 minutes.
Add orange peel.
Sift whole-wheat flour with salt. Gradually stir in egg and honey.
Add wine and olive oil, stirring constantly, as small amounts are added.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Line the bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan with oiled parchment or a brown paper shopping bag.
Oil the pan and paper well.
Pour in batter and bake for 20 minutes.
Turn oven off and let cake sit for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Turn over and detach from spring pan carefully.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Partially
cook
broccoli.
Arrange
on
bottom
of
a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cook, bone and cut up chicken.
Mix
all	ingredients and add to chicken.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with 1 cup of crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350°
for
30 minutes until bubbly and slightly brown.
Canned asparagus
spears
can be substituted and 1 can of soup can be cream of mushroom.

title: quick jambalaya(for a crowd)
directions: Put chopped
vegetables
and
butter
in
a large heavy Dutch oven.
Cook vegetables until soft over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients
in
the
order
listed.
Stir to blend. Bring to a boil
and
reduce heat.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.	Add additional chicken
broth
if the liquid is absorbed before the rice is done.
Use	as
many
shrimp
as you like, fresh or canned. Serves 16.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Combine ham, margarine, mustard and onion.
Put into rolls. Layer on cheese.
Cover with top of roll.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and bake about 10 minutes at 350°, until warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour, salt, cocoa and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Use egg whites on top.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, while beating.
Crush vanilla wafers and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for one hour and fifteen minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple.
Bring to a boil; simmer 3 minutes, then cool.
Cream together cheese, sugar and baby food; fold into cooled jello mixture.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate until serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, spices and salt.
Add milk and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until blade of knife comes out clean.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in large bowl.
Chill one hour.
Stir and serve.
You can add other fruit if you desire.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add eggs, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add zucchini last.
Mix well; place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Wrap in plastic wrap; let stand overnight before slicing.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Clean out center of bread to make it look like a bowl. Mix together remaining ingredients. Pour into shell of bread. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Use pieces of bread to dip in filling. Excellent.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir well. Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth. Blend in Cool Whip and peaches. Chill if necessary until mix will mound, then spoon into crust. Chill about 3 hours, until firm.

title: eggplant disguise
directions: Mix all together; put in baking pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly, at 350°.
No one will ever know it's eggplant!

title: dump cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given. Do not mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple peanut butter crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apple slices in bottom of a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix lemon juice and water and pour over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Mix remaining ingredients over the apples.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening and shredded cheese until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mixes better with the fingers than with a fork.
Add milk; stir until dampened.
Drop into a greased cookie sheet by heaping teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: silly putty
directions: Put in bowl and have children work with their hands. This can take quite a while.
Have them squish through their fingers until ready to play with.

title: spatzle
directions: Stir together flour and salt in a bowl.
Blend egg and milk; stir into flour mixture.
Place 1/2 the dough in a strainer.
Hold over boiling salted water.
With a spatula, press dough through the strainer to form the Spatzle.
Repeat with remaining dough. Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Great with any kind of soup or just by themselves with butter on them.

title: gravy for meatballs
directions: Melt butter in skillet with drippings.
Stir in flour.
Add beef bouillon cube dissolved in boiling water and instant coffee powder.
Cook and stir until gravy thickens.
Add meatballs. Cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes, basting occasionally. Makes 30 balls.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl combine sugars, flour and cinnamon.
Add fruit.
Mix well, turn into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover and cut slits into crust.
Seal edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and spread on shallow pan or tray (pizza pan).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a buttered 2-quart casserole, put the 3 cups chopped cabbage.
Brown meat and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice, tomato soup and water to mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes, then pour over cabbage.
Don't stir.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and put in bottom of buttered pie pan. Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in sugar.
Add yolks one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Stir in lemon juice.
Fold in cream after it is stiffly beaten.
Pour in pan and sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs over top.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Remove skins from potatoes; shred into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup of butter.
Shred cheese and mix with potatoes.
Stir in soup, sour cream and onion with butter.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cornflakes and drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: greek chicken lemon soup
directions: Quarter chickens.
Cover with water.
Simmer three hours or more.
Remove chicken.
Strain stock.
Finely chop onion.
Add onion and rice to stock.
Simmer until rice splits.
Allow stock to cool for 1/2 hour.

title: ketchup cocktail wieners
directions: In a crock-pot, mix all ingredients, except hot dogs, stirring well.
Cut hot dogs into thirds and add to crock-pot.
Heat on high until mixture begins to bubble; reduce heat to low and serve in crock-pot.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a heavy saucepan.
Add water and stir until well blended.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Stir in mixture while gradually adding the milk.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. (Cook about 3 to 5 minutes.) Remove from heat; add the vanilla and pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: sauerkraut and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain.
Crumble. Saute onion in bacon grease until wilted but not brown.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes, brown sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add bacon.
Serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Begin 1 1/2 hours ahead.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, fry bacon until almost crisp; push to side of pan.
Add onions and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add carrots, celery and parsley; cook 5 minutes.
Add water, potatoes, clam liquid, tomatoes with their liquid, bay leaf, salt, thyme and pepper; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
With sharp knife, chop clams; add to vegetable mixture; gently simmer soup 5 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings, or 14 cups.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put in blender and blend for 2 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator 10 days.

title: william's squirrel dumplings
directions: Cook squirrels in a large pot of water.
Continue cooking until you can pierce meat with a fork.
Add soup mix and cook until meat is tender.
Roll biscuits in flour and pinch off small amounts; drop into simmering liquid.
Cook 45 minutes, then let pot sit for 45 minutes.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large skillet, cook bacon 1 minute.
Add beef and onion and cook.
Drain off excess fat.
Add ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar, stirring to blend.
Spoon mixture into a 3-quart casserole and add remaining ingredients, stirring lightly to blend.
Bake 1 hour.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup coconut.

title: dip
directions: Brown turkey and hamburger.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and salsa.
Mix together and let simmer.
Put in casserole dish and put sour cream and cheeses on top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain grease.
Stir in water and seasoning mix.
Mash pinto beans; pour into hamburger mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Layer taco chips in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over crushed taco chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top each serving with diced lettuce and tomato.
Top with taco sauce if desired.

title: chewy choco-chip cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in bowl with wire whisk.
In another bowl mix together sugars.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla to sugars. Add flour mixture to sugar batter.
Mix in 2 cups of milk chocolate chips, semi-sweet chocolate chips, white choco-chips, walnuts, pecans, or Macadamia nuts in any desired combination. Preheat oven to 300°.
Use an ice cream scoop to make large, chewy cookies.
Bake slowly 20 to 24 minutes.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 9-inch pan. In bowl, mix in 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour over oleo. Do not stir. Pour 1 can of unsweetened cherries (or substitute any fruit) evenly over batter.
Sprinkle rest of sugar (1/2 cup) over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. (Note: Fruit will go to bottom and crust will form on top.)

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
Crisco; add egg and syrup.
Sift dry ingredients in flour and add to first mixture.
Roll in balls; dip in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add egg and beat until light. Blend in cocoa, vanilla and orange juice.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, oats, raisins and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove onto wire racks to cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add flour and nuts.
Put in a greased pan and sprinkle with the chocolate or butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix until creamy.
Add eggs; mix well. Add carrots and pineapple.
Mix flour with dry ingredients; stir into carrot mixture.
Mixing thoroughly, beat on high for 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan, or can use a 10-inch tube tin, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: dirt pudding
directions: With food processor, crumble cookies.
Remove 1 cup and set aside.
To remaining crumbs, add margarine and press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze 15 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping until light and fluffy. Gently spread mixture over chilled crumbs.
Beat pudding and milk together; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Stir in egg whites until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.
If desired, spread with cream cheese frosting. Cut into bars.
Refrigerate
bars.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread evenly in a baking dish.

title: sweet and spicy baked beans
directions: Saute onion in drippings from bacon. Add to remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Remove top.
Stir and bake an additional 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chili rellenos(stuffed hot peppers)
directions: Wash and dry poblano peppers.
Coat peppers slightly with vegetable oil.
Fry on top of stove on flat griddle turning constantly (or in oven broiler turning constantly at 350°) until skin appears to be dark and peeling off.
Remove from griddle and place all peppers in medium-sized paper bag for 10 minutes (makes skin easier to peel off).
Peel off skin (use gloves if necessary) carefully.
Make a 2-inch slit in each pepper and stuff with half slice of cheese (or other meat filling).
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold in beaten egg yolks carefully.
Roll peppers in flour, then in egg white mixture.
Fry until egg batter is set in deep frying pan with hot oil.
Peel tomatoes and blend in blender with chiles and broth.
Serve over stuffed peppers.

title: betty brown's cheesecake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg, vanilla and water to hold pastry together.
Pat into spring-form pan with floured hands.

title: hot dog in a roll(great kids dish)
directions: Roll hot dog in shell with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in half the chicken broth for 5 to 8 minutes in a medium saucepan.
In a very large pan, add the remaining broth, broccoli, mustard seed and dill weed.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes. Blend cooked cauliflower, broth and mace in blender until smooth. Cook onion in butter until tender; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir cauliflower mixture and onion mixture together with the broccoli mixture in the large saucepan.
Add milk and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Place pastry in pie pan.
Trim and flute, but do not prick. Beat eggs slightly, just enough to mix yolks and whites.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in milk, then add flavoring.

Pour into pie shell. Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until crust browns; then reduce heat to slow 300° oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until pie is set to within 1/2-inch from center.
Test by gently shaking.
You can see how much of the center is still liquid.
An inch of the liquid area in center will finish cooking after pie is removed from oven.
Cool on wire rack before serving.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Add all other ingredients, except vanilla and butter.
Cook until well mixed and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipping cream or Cool Whip.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and cook in a small amount of water until almost done.
Drain and sprinkle with sugar.
Set aside.
Melt 2 Tbsp butter and add the flour and milk to make a white sauce.
In a separate pan melt the rest of the butter and stir into the cracker crumbs.
Put cabbage in baking dish, pour white sauce over it. Put the crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 min.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into three or four 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° for about 50 or 60 minutes or until crust is golden brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Can freeze.

title: quick-n-easy quiche
directions: Melt butter in pan; set aside.
Mix together eggs, milk and Bisquick.
Heat oven to 375°.
Add Cheddar cheese, then add onion. Add melted butter.
Pour mixture into ungreased glass pie plate. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and more milk if necessary. Chill and serve with chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water until thermometer reaches 236°.
Add peanuts and cook slowly until thermometer reaches 294°. Remove from heat and add soda and salt and mix well.
Pour into well-buttered jelly roll pan.
When cool, break into pieces. Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: baked flounder
directions: Mix bread crumbs, onion and celery.
Salt and pepper to taste. Saute in butter until onion and celery are softened.
Place dark skinned fillets in foil-lined pan, divide dressing evenly and top with light skinned fillets.
Place 3 half strips of bacon on top of each.
Place in oven preheated to 450° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serves a multitude.

title: baked gouda
directions: Cut cheese round in half crosswise to form 2 circles; remove wax.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one rectangle on top of second; repeat with remaining rectangles.
Press each into a 6-inch square; place cheese circle in center of each.
Pull corners of dough to top center of cheese.
Press dough tightly against center to seal, twisting off excess dough.
Brush with beaten egg.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Chill.

title: orient express cookie squares
directions: Combine white sugar, brown sugar and flour in food processor. Add coffee, vanilla, almond extract and margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spread dough on an ungreased jelly roll pan (may have to press with fingers).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet pizza dough(to make 2 pizzas)
directions: Cover sugar and shortening with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add a pinch of sugar.
Add yeast to first mixture.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in well-greased bowl and cover.
Set in refrigerator; let stand for at least 12 hours, or let rise on countertop for approximately 6 hours.
Dough must double in size.
Press into greased pan.
Add your favorite pizza sauce and toppings.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together; then add to butter mixture.
Fold in nuts and pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Line a pan with sliced peaches.
Make a batter.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch and pour batter along with 1 cup of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bacon bread sticks
directions: Dredge one side of bacon in cheese.
Roll it, cheese side in, around bread sticks.
Place sticks on a thick paper towel lined serving platter.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes, until bacon is done.
Roll again in cheese.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and cut in bite-size pieces.
Place in large baking pan.
Cover with undiluted chicken soup.
Then place dumplings which have been cooked in the chicken broth after chicken has been removed.
Add some broth over dumplings in baking dish.
Make crust.
Roll out thin and cut in strips.
Cover mixture with strips, lattice style.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and stir to thicken like gravy. Add soup and mayonnaise.
Layer peeled and sliced potatoes and onions in dish. Pour sauce over. Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: meatballs with rice
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1/2-inch meatballs.
Brown meatballs and place into casserole dish. Mix next 6 ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese is melted and lightly brown.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.

title: watergate salad
directions: To pistachio pudding, add crushed pineapple.
Stir. Let thicken.
Then add marshmallows and nuts.

title: noel chicken
directions: Place chicken skin side up in pan.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not overcover.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Section rabbit and dust with salt and pepper.
Flour the pieces and brown in grease or oil.
Add water and cover skillet. Turn rabbit several times and continue cooking at low heat until tender.
Remove and serve with mashed potatoes, gravy and a vegetable.

title: surprise cherry squares
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually add flour, beating well.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts (no salt).
Save broth.
Dip tortillas in broth and line baking dish with tortillas.
Bone chicken and place on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle chili powder, onion, cheese and garlic salt over this.
Spread soups over this.
Spread the tomatoes and green chilies.
Bake in glass baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti according to directions.
Drain.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Blend all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated, approximately 20 minutes.

title: roast turkey
directions: Remove giblets and rinse turkey thoroughly with cold water; pat dry.
Sprinkle cavity with salt.
Tie ends of legs to tail with cord or string or tuck them under flap of skin around tail.
Lift wingtips up and over back so they are tucked under bird.
Brush entire bird with melted butter.
Place on a roasting rack, breast side up.
Insert meat thermometer in breast or meat part of thigh, making sure it does not touch bone.
Bake at 325° until meat thermometer reaches 185° (about 4 1/2 to 5 hours).

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water (1 cup).
Dissolve cranberry sauce in other cup boiling water; add other ingredients and refrigerate until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: no-bake bars
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
(Add more oats if you do not want coconut.)
Pour into prepared pan. Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator. Makes approximately 36 bars.

title: raisin upside-down cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening, milk, egg and raisins. Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and boiling water.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and dressing mix.
Roll into ball and roll in bacon bits.

title: spicy vegetable-beef stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard and stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside. Cut the broccoli into bite-size pieces.
In a nonstick wok or large nonstick skillet, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, onion and garlic and stir-fry until the vegetables are crisp-tender and the onion begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir the cornstarch mixture again and pour it into the wok.
Stir in the beef, peanuts, red pepper flakes and black pepper and stir-fry until the sauce thickens and the beef is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
If necessary, reduce the heat to keep the sauce from evaporating.
Calories:
200, fat 9 g and sodium 240 mg.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
30 minutes.

title: red rouser
directions: Place ice cream in tall glass.
Fill glass with cranberry juice.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice and stir until thick.
Fold in one cup of fruit and pour into pastry shell.
Cover with whipped cream and garnish with remaining berries.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Microwave for 5 minutes Veg-All.
Melt butter and Cheez Whiz together.
Mix this with Veg-All and add Ritz crackers.
Stir together and bake at 350° until thick.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Place 4 pepperoni strips on each rectangle.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Starting at shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle; pinch to seal. Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16 pinwheels.

title: orange-pineapple mold
directions: In a saucepan, drain pineapple.
Measure juice and add water to make 2 cups.
Add cream cheese.

Let it come to a boiling point, stirring so cream cheese is all melted. Add to Jell-O and stir until all is dissolved. Add pineapple and evaporated milk. Pour into medium Tupperware mold sprayed lightly with Pam. Refrigerate.
May use dressing of a little Cool Whip and mayonnaise, but salad is rich enough without.
Yields 10 servings.

title: herbed cheese biscuits
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix flour, baking powder, dill and salt. With a fork, cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Add milk and stir just enough to hold dough together.
Place on a lightly floured surface and knead lightly; roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter without turning the biscuit cutter (push straight down) and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until as brown as desired.
Yield:
Twelve 2-inch biscuits.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add milk.
Sift flour and soda together and add to mixture. Fold in bananas.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° for one hour.

title: sausage minestrone
directions: In large kettle, brown sausage, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except green beans and spaghetti.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Stir in beans and spaghetti.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with remaining ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables (carrot slices, celery slices, mushrooms, radishes, cucumber slices, cauliflower, etc.).

title: nan's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until barely tender (al dente).
Drain; cool in running cold water.
Drain well.
Mix together celery, onion, pepper, cheese and tuna.
Layer macaroni in thirds with layer of mix and 1/3 mayonnaise and vinegar.
Mix gently.
Chill.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fish or seafood.

title: quick dessert
directions: Put fruit in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar. Add 1 stick oleo; cut into flour as for pie crust.
Add egg.
Dough will not be smooth.
Scatter dough mixture over fruit.
Bake about 40 minutes or until crust is brown at 375° to 400°.
Serve with topping or plain.
Use any kind of fruit, berries or rhubarb.

title: georgia's pasta salad
directions: Cook garlic in oil for 1 minute.
Add onions and bell peppers. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add wine and olives.
Boil wine until reduced by half.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in cooked rotelle.
Season with basil to taste.

title: jello fig jam
directions: Wash, drain, peel and mash figs.
Mix sugar and jello.
Pour over figs and let stand for 45 minutes.
Stir over medium heat. Bring to a good rolling boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 can of chili, 2 tablespoons onion and 1 cup of cheese. Spoon 1/3 cup of mixture on center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in an ungreased baking dish (11 x 7-inch). Spoon remaining chili over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining onion and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Heat applesauce. Stir in soda. Add alternately with sifted flour, spices and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased muffin tins until light brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Batter will keep, covered, in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas, chicken and 1/3 cup cheese.
Pour some sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch or larger pan. In each tortilla, place chicken cubes and sauce.
Roll up and put in pan seam side down.
When pan is full, pour remaining sauce over top.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: classic mexican burrito
directions: In a pan over medium high heat add vegetable oil.
Mix the ground beef in the pan with the soy sauce and the sliced peppers. Add the rest of the seasonings according to your taste.
Not too much though!
While the beef is cooking peel the potatoes and cut them in small squares.
When the beef has turned brown completely, add the water and the tomato sauce.
Cover the pan but keep on mixing constantly until the potatoes are soft.
Heat up the tortillas and put some beef in center.
Roll it up and ENJOY!

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine flour, powdered sugar and 1 cup butter; press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: grandma cora's flatbread
directions: Blend dry ingredients; cut in margarine as in pie crust.
Add 1 cup of buttermilk.
Blend thoroughly, but don't overmix.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook all together until vegetables are done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Simmer soup and water.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; beat on low speed until lumps dissolve. Add mayo, gelatin, vegetables and shrimp.
Stir until blended. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: minestrone soup(no meat)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 4 tablespoons olive oil. Add can of chicken broth and 3 1/2 cans of water.
Add all ingredients except macaroni, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bring to a

boil and simmer 15 minutes. Add macaroni. Cook until tender. Add parsley and Parmesan cheese during the last few minutes of cooking time. Seasoned salt and a few drops of Tabasco sauce (to your taste) makes this recipe extra special.

title: taco meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 15 to 20 small balls.
Place in covered glass casserole bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, turning over in dish once.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: cheese cache chicken
directions: Cut pocket in each chicken piece, making a 2-inch deep slit in side.
Place strip of Jack cheese and sage in each pocket.
Chill. Beat eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and parsley together. Roll breasts in flour and dip in egg batter.
Heat butter in skillet.
Saute breasts until crisp and golden, turning with spatula.
Transfer chicken to baking dish and bake in preheated 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: golden glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook, covered in boiling water, 15 minutes. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cook, stirring, about 8 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour and add the lemon juice and rind, slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and salt.
Stir in the skim milk and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the first mixture.
Pour into custard cups and bake or the sponge may also be baked in a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet onion sandwich(don't miss this one)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown and saute onions over medium heat until brown, adding garlic salt and black pepper while cooking.
Spray one side of bread slices with nonstick cooking spray and toast.
Place thick pile of cooked onions on 2 slices of toast and top with 1 slice cheese.
Warm at 375° long enough to melt cheese.
Top with bread slice and serve warm.
Recipe makes 2 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: parmesan chicken bake(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides.
Melt margarine in baking dish in oven.
Add chicken, turning to coat both sides with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Has 219 calories per 2 halves.

title: baked stew
directions: Put items into a large pot, in the order listed and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add applesauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: weight watchers cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool.
Blend cottage cheese in mixer or blender.
Stir into cooled Jell-O and add Cool Whip. Can pour into graham cracker pie crust or into Pyrex pie pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the oil, sugar and eggs.
To creamed mixture, add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon sifted together.
Mix well and add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Grease and line with wax paper in a tube pan. Cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Can top with Caramel Icing or plain.

title: beef and broccoli stir fry
directions: In a bowl combine tomato sauce, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger. Set aside.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each addition until blended.
Stir in oats,
Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: shrimply divine mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup and add gelatin, stirring until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in mayonnaise, cream cheese, shrimp, onions and celery.
Pour into mold.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherries in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until light and fluffy. Mix flour with soda and salt; add to butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chunks, nuts and coconut. Chill 1 hour. Drop onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, add rice, vegetables and spices. In skillet, brown chicken in 5 tablespoons oleo.
Remove pieces. Drain off fat.
Add soup and water to frying pan.
Bring to boil. Scrape up bottom of pan.
Put chicken on rice.
Add soup mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken, then shred it.
Put shredded chicken in a pan, then mix 1/2 cup enchilada sauce and salt as you like.
The rest of the sauce put in another pan and warm it.
Fry tortillas just enough to soften (not crisp), then dip in the sauce and fill with chicken.
Roll it and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top enchiladas with onion and cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crab-mushroom filling for crepes
directions: Bone and flake crab meat (drain well if using canned).
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken stock gradually, stirring continuously.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Add crab and mushrooms.
Let heat thoroughly.
Add cheese, wine and seasonings.

title: bajou broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli according to package directions. Saute onions and celery in small amount of butter (oleo) in skillet.
Combine sauteed vegetables, rice, broccoli and butter. Melt Cheez Whiz in soup with 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Stir in broccoli mixture, blending well.
Place into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil until bubbling; then mix in flour with a spoon. Add baking powder, salt, cinnamon and vanilla and mix well. Stir in apples and walnuts. Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and pour in mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until lightly golden brown.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Combine above ingredients and form into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown quickly in shortening.
Arrange meat balls in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover well with mixed sauce.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage, season to taste.
Drain.
Saute in skillet butter and onion.
Remove from heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together until melted.
Mix with cabbage and pour into a greased glass Pyrex dish.
Top with Ritz crackers. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: quick peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese, peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts, or spoon chocolate syrup over when serving.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Beat the butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts and chill in refrigerator.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around Kisses.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: coconut mochi
directions: *To lower fat:
Substitute skim evaporated milk and 1 tablespoon coconut extract.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Drain and chop chilies.
Mix other ingredients, except cheese, and pour 1/2 of the mixture into a hot skillet.
Sprinkle cheese and green chilies over it.
Pour the remaining mixture over it and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Very good.

title: frito salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat, set aside and let cool.
Combine lettuce, cucumbers, tomatoes and cheese.
When meat is cool, add to salad mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve. Add Catalina dressing and Fritos just before serving, then serve immediately.

title: meat and "tater" pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine and mix gently all ingredients but potatoes.
Lightly pat in pastry.
Top with potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Seal top crust and split.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ketchup.

title: no peek chicken and rice
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine rice, can of soup, onion soup mix blended with water.
Arrange chicken on soup mixture.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours until chicken is tender and rice is done.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chocolate ritz dipped cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave.
Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Dip crackers in chocolate (coat all of crackers with chocolate).
Place on waxed paper and let cool.
Chocolate will harden.
Can use white chocolate.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Add pecans to remainder of sour cream mixture.
Spread between layers of cake, split side up. Combine reserved sour cream mixture with whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spread on cake and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Peel, quarter, core and slice apples.
Mix together the 4 tablespoons sugar with the 2 teaspoons cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs; add 2 cups sugar and beat in oil.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add with orange juice.
Add vanilla.
Layer batter, apples, cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Repeat.
End with batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until tested done (it usually takes about 15 to 20 minutes longer).

title: chicken chili
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry. Remove visible fat. Cut chicken in 1/2-inch pieces. In large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken in hot oil until meat is lightly browned. Add onion, celery and garlic; cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes, stirring to break up. Add all remaining ingredients. Cover and allow to simmer for 10 minutes. Remove cover and simmer 15 minutes or until part of the liquid evaporates and chili thickens. Makes 6 servings.

title: quick crab dip
directions: Microwave crab meat and mayo 1 minute.
Add Cheddar; microwave 1 minute.
Add the chopped onion; microwave 30 seconds.
Serve with crackers.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 3 cups hot water.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator until set.
Cut marshmallows.
Dissolve lemon juice in 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows and melt in hot jello.
Combine pineapple, cream cheese, mayonnaise, whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Combine with the lemon jello.
Pour over congealed lime jello.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix ingredients, except soup, well;
shape in a narrow loaf pan.
Let it set for at least 8 hours or overnight.
Cut in slices and fry until brown.
Put slices in layers in a roaster or flat baking dish.
Spread the soup on each piece (use one whole can). Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: jewish hospital's chunky chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.

title: pork chops a l'orange
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Drain mandarin oranges, reserving juice and setting fruit aside.
Combine 1/2 cup of juice with remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add oranges last 5 minutes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Spread butter in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Place chicken in middle.
Sprinkle rice around chicken.
Place carrots and broccoli over rice.
Add water until full.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 6 tablespoons juice.
Combine flour, sugar and pineapple juice (6 tablespoons).
Add cheese and pineapple tidbits.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: To melt chocolate pieces:
Put in dish and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium (5) for 4 to 6 minutes.
Check after 4 and 5 minutes to see if they are melted.
Do not microwave too long.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, with squash.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabin she crab soup
directions: Heat milk in double boiler until almost boiling (scalded). Melt butter in saucepan; add flour gradually and whip until smooth.
Quickly add to scalded milk and stir until smooth.
Thin with boiling water.
Add chicken base, spices and lemon juice. Add wine and crabmeat.
Thin soup to consistency with cold milk. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: chicken broakridge
directions: In a 9 by 13 inch pan, place cut up chicken pieces.
Add 2 layers of cheese and crushed croutons.
Mix together broth and sherry; pour over chicken, cheese and croutons. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; remove cover and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook
hamburger
until	crumbly.
Add
package	of taco sauce, following directions on package.
Cool.
Chop tomatoes; shred lettuce.
Layer as follows in a large bowl:
hamburger, lettuce, tomatoes,
cheese
and chips.
Repeat one more time. Eat salad with taco sauce and sour cream.

title: molded tuna mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in lemon juice in large mixer bowl. Add broth. Stir to dissolve gelatin. Add next 7 ingredients. Beat until well mixed. Chill 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Beat until frothy. Fold in tuna and cucumber. Turn into 2-cup mold. Chill 3 hours or until firm. Serves 4.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and beat stiff, but not dry.
Cut dates and nuts in cracker crumbs and fold into mixture.
Add flavoring.
Bake in greased pie pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: international pork
directions: Cut pork tenderloin into 1/8-inch thick slices by 1/2-inch wide.
Marinate in Italian salad dressing overnight.
Clean green pepper and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Clean Spanish onion and cut into slices.
Cut 16 Greek olives into quarters.
In small bowl, add olives, 1 tablespoon Chinese hot mustard, 1/4 cup soy sauce and 1/2 cup salsa sauce.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas (I use largest size).
Roll up and let set overnight.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in vanilla wafer crumbs and baking powder.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour or more at 325°. Let cool thoroughly in pan.

title: peanut butter cookies (no bake)
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup until dissolved on stove or microwave.
Add peanut butter and stir in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and then mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour in baking dish.
Crumble package of Ritz crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: elegant beef(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Put beef in slow-cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover tightly and cook at "low" for 8 to 10 hours; on "high" for 4 to 5 hours.
Add 1 tablespoon Kitchen Bouquet to darken gravy, if you wish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Cream the cream cheese and pineapple.
When smooth, add 1 cup pecans, pepper, onions and seasoned salt.
Chill mixture well.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill until served.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cut up and cook first three ingredients until done.
Put through sieve.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Boil for 1 hour. Put in jars and seal.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna fish with mayonnaise and pickles.
Mix well.
Put in bowl in center.
Cut lettuce in small pieces and add cheese, tomatoes and pineapple.
Combine well.
Put around tuna.
Serve with dressing and you'll have a good salad.
Chill before eating.

title: puffed pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a blender on medium speed, mix the eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon until just combined, about 15 seconds.
The batter should be a little lumpy. Melt the butter or margarine in a 12-inch cast-iron skillet or ovenproof skillet by putting it in the hot oven for about 30 seconds.
Remove the skillet from oven; spread butter to coat bottom and sides and pour in batter.
Return the skillet to oven and bake for about 20 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned. Cut into wedges and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: chicken creamy casserole
directions: Chop cooked chicken.
Cook rice according to package directions. Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Press cooked rice into the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture on top.
Sprinkle the top with cheese and black olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until hot.
Dab several more teaspoons of sour cream after removed from oven.
Serves 8.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Cream together by hand.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: pam's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Saute stems, oil, butter, bread cubes, garlic, salt, basil, oregano and salt.
Fill caps with mix.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender for 1 minute.
Grease and flour 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Delicious with or without whipped cream or whipped topping.
Makes own crust.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and onion powder and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
In a large bowl mix the meat, lettuce, cheese, beans, tomatoes, Fritos and dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: ash cake(50 years or older)
directions: Add sugar to sifted corn meal.
Make up with water and knead well.
Make into round, flat cakes.

title: cranberry sauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
