Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan. Sift together dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add remaining cranberry sauce, nuts, real mayonnaise and orange rind.
Mix well by hand.
Stir in orange juice.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan while warm.
Cool and frost with:

title: grape jam
directions: Bring beet juice, Kool-Aid and Sure-Jell to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Add sugar and boil for 1 minute.
Put in jars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together except pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serves 12.

title: swiss cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Use as a hot dip for Ritz crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray Pam lightly in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish or pan. Press crescent rolls into bottom of pan; sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. You can sprinkle Cajun spice or Italian seasonings over cheese before baking for spicy flavor.
Makes 8 servings.

title: elbow macaroni creole
directions: Fry sausage and remove from pan, saving 4 tablespoons fat. Saute onions and pepper; add tomatoes and seasonings and simmer 15 minutes.
Add sausage.
Cook elbow macaroni.
Alternate layers of macaroni and sausage mixture.
Bake with bread crumbs on top at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread one side of each slice of bread with margarine and the other side with salad dressing.
With the margarine side down, top four slices of bread with corned beef or cooked beef, Swiss cheese and sauerkraut.
Top with remaining bread slices, dressing side down.
In a large skillet, cook 2 of the sandwiches over medium-low heat for 4 to 6 minutes or until the bread toasts and the cheese melts, turning once.
Repeat with remaining sandwiches. Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown meat, celery and onions in oil.
Add rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cook for 2 hours.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix and cook in layers at 350° until done.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar. Add seasoning and bring to a boil.
Add cucumber, pepper and onion. Let boil 2 minutes. Pack boiling hot in jars and seal.

title: fruit cake
directions: Heat milk, adding marshmallows; stir until smooth.
Mix cracker crumbs, fruit and nuts together.
Pour marshmallow mixture over other ingredients, mixing well.
Pack firmly into pan lined with wax paper.
(I use mini loaf pans.) Put in refrigerator and chill.
When cold, peel wax paper off and wrap with plastic.
Can be kept in refrigerator or frozen for later use.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Season chicken according to taste; place in Pyrex dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup, together with wine and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove chicken and place in serving dish. Pour the sauce from the Pyrex into a pan; add the sour cream. Heat on slow fire for a few minutes.
Add nutmeg to suit your taste.
Pour the velvety white sauce over the chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: granny's grapefruit and ginger salad
directions: Let Jell-O begin
to
set
(follow directions on Jell-O box for using
fruit).	Before	adding	fruit,	nuts,
celery, apples and ginger.
Mix
well
and
place into 3 cup mold; let set until firm.
Serve on a bed of lettuce;
cut in squares.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute butter and onion until onion is tender.
Thaw broccoli and drain.
Add to onion.
Combine Jiffy mix, eggs and sour cream. Add butter mixture and stir well.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: greek vegetables
directions: Saute zucchini, eggplant and onion in oil and butter.
Add fresh vegetables and rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat until tender.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for about 1 hour (if too thick, may add tomato juice.)
Better the 2nd day, if any left.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Press a roll of cookie dough in 9 x 9 pan. Next, put a layer of coconut on top of dough. Add a bag of chocolate chips, then a cup of pecans. Pour Eagle Brand milk on top of mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: In a large bowl, cream 1/2 cup butter.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar. Add egg; mix well.
Sift in 2 cups of flour, baking powder and salt, adding alternately with milk.
Spoon into a greased shallow 9 x 9-inch pan.
Distribute berries evenly over dough.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup flour.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut remaining butter into mixture.
Break into large crumbs and sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Melt 1/4 pound oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour batter into pan on top of oleo. Top batter with one large can of sliced peaches and bake in 325° oven until batter rises to top.
After batter has risen to top, but before it is brown, sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture on top. Total baking time is 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pork chops monterey
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil. Remove chops. Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Stir in tomatoes, water, rice and seasoning. Add chops. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until water is absorbed. Stir occasionally.
Remove chops and stir 1 cup cheese in rice.
Top with chops and remaining cheese.

title: quaker's prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: date and banana pudding
directions: Use individual glass serving dishes.
Alternate layers of banana and dates.
Cover with cream.
Serve cold.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Beat yolks in separate bowl.
Beat whites until frothy.
Fold together with salt and pepper to taste.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Layer chiles, cheese to top of dish.
Pour eggs slowly over chiles covering entirely.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: *Cream cheese needs to be room temperature.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 melba toast with 1/2 Tablespoon of milk.
Set aside. Beat egg yolks.
Add melba mixture.
Add shrimp, cottage cheese, onion, celery, cayenne pepper, parsley and salt.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into shrimp mixture.
Spray baking dish heavily with pam.
Sprinkle top with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake 1 hour or more until set.
This is a single serving recipe.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all together; put on top of lettuce.

title: lemon blender cookies
directions: Trim a thin slice from both ends of unpeeled lemon; cut in half lengthwise.
With a shallow V shaped cut, remove white center core. Cut halves in small chunks.
In electric blender, puree lemon chunks with water.
Add shortening and egg; blend until smooth.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and lemon mixture; mix well.
Drop batter from teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: fluffy salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O in Cool Whip.
Add the other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, gradually adding sugar a little at a time. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shells.
Add pie filling on top of mixture (any pie filling will do).

title: creole pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, in saucepan and boil for 15 minutes.

Then begin testing for drop-ball test in cool water. After soft ball stage, remove from heat for about 10 minutes or until it starts to granulate; then pour onto a buttered surface or aluminum foil in praline size rounds, and add pecans at once.
Let cool.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Beat first 10 ingredients together.
Stir in remaining.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Cool.
Frost with whipped cream.

title: corned beef on bun
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put between hamburger buns.
Top with cheese slices and wrap in foil.
Put in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: chocolate fudge pies
directions: Melt margarine, blend by hand cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in sugar, eggs (one at a time) and milk.
Pour into 2 unbaked (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes more.
Do not cook real firm, just until center feels like jello.

title: country wieners
directions: Slice wieners, onions and peppers.
Lightly brown wieners in hot oil in skillet.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet, cook remaining ingredients until tender, stirring often.
Add wieners and heat thoroughly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and cool to lukewarm.
Cook until thick, sugar, flour, vinegar and water.
Add mayonnaise and mustard; beat and pour over macaroni.
Add hard-boiled eggs, onion, celery, carrots or whatever you like.

title: western dressing
directions: Mix all well and store in a jar with a cover.

title: saturday night supper
directions: Cook noodles and place in casserole.
Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until vegetables are just limp.
Add soups, sour cream and corn; mix well.
cook until bubbling, then pour over noodles.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Grated cheese may be added as topping.

title: palacinke(serbian crepes)
directions: Warm milk and water on stove; add flour, sugar, salt, vanilla extract and eggs into large bowl with warmed milk and water. Batter should be very thin consistency.
Cover 6-inch skillet with Pam or oil.
Drip enough batter onto thinly covered surface and fry over medium heat.
Turn over once until brown on both sides.

title: refreshing fruit punch
directions: In a blender, combine raspberries or strawberries, peaches, lemonade and bananas (thaw first if frozen) with 1/2 cup cold water.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Sieve mixture and discard seeds.
Stir in 2 cups cold water.
Serve immediately or chill and stir before serving.
Makes 8 servings (6 oz. each).

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into microwave-safe bowl.
Cut up stick of butter on top; microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add nuts if you prefer. Pour into a buttered square dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then cut into squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until
light
and fluffy.
Beat 1 egg at a time in mixture adding flour and sour cream alternately starting with flour and
ending with flour.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Pour into greased
and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender but firm (either on stove or in microwave).
Put cooked broccoli in casserole.
Add soup, milk, bread crumbs or croutons and mix well.
Rip or cut up the cheese slices and arrange on top.
Put in oven at 350° and heat until bubbly.

title: fudge
directions: Boil evaporated milk and sugar in saucepan for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to cool completely and cut into pieces.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Cut cooked chicken in small pieces. Make gravy with broth.
Mix in cheese; mix all together.
Then put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbles and hot.
Serves 20.

title: macaroni and cheese custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
(Can add more macaroni/cracker crumbs, if desired.)

title: cabbage deviled eggs
directions: Use enough mayonnaise to make smooth.

title: individual oreo cheesecakes
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until creamy. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended.
Gently stir in chopped cookies. Spoon evenly into foil cup-lined medium muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set. Cool completely. Refrigerate several minutes or until chilled.

title: pie filling
directions: To Blueberries: 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir vigorously until mix leaves side of bowl.
Press dough in bowl and make a ball.
Knead 10 times to make smooth.
On lightly floured surface, roll out to a 13-inch circle.
Place on pizza pan.
Turn up edge 1/2-inch and pinch.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon salad oil, then put on topping in order given.

title: party beans
directions: Brown ground beef with the chopped onion.
Drain off excess fat.
In crock-pot mix ground beef, pork and beans, kidney beans, butter beans and bacon bits.
Mix in ketchup, mustard and brown sugar (vary amounts to suit personal taste).
Cook in crock-pot until hot.

title: fancy fowl
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly combine onion recipe soup mix, apricot preserves and water; set aside.
In a foil-lined broiler pan, arrange chicken breasts and peppers; top with soup mixture. Broil 7 inches from heat 10 minutes or until chicken is done, turning once.
Serve over hot rice.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Gradually add the mayonnaise to the cream cheese until smooth. Add dash of salt and the lemon juice.
Add the chopped walnuts, maraschino cherries, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Fold in the Dream Whip that has been made by directions on package.
Freeze in a 2-quart oblong Pyrex dish.
This keeps in freezer for a long time.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Add cheese to noodles. Mix with spaghetti sauce and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: that's it!
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over pineapple; mix well.
Add cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
That's it!

title: beth's no carrot stew
directions: Cut kielbasa or sausage into bits less than one-inch long. Chop onions, slice mushrooms and cut potatoes into chunks.
Put all into large pot.
Add two cans mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water or beer.
Stir and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add green beans and cook an additional 1/2 hour.

title: vermicelli vinaigrette salad
directions: Cook the vermicelli according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain and set aside.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving 1/4 cup marinade.
Chop artichoke hearts.
Combine vermicelli, artichoke hearts, tomatoes, mushrooms, nuts and parsley.
Mix well and set aside. Combine reserved marinade, oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, basil and pepper in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over vermicelli mixture; toss gently. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve ingredients in 2 cups hot water and stir until clear. Add 2 cups cold water.
Pour in holders or plastic cups and freeze.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix in skillet and pour into buttered baking dish. Top with corn flakes.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O and water together and 1 cup pineapple juice. Add pineapple and cherry pie filling. Mix together.
Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip together; pour onto Jell-O. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: spicy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and set aside.
In mixing bowl, gradually add sugar to batter, creaming well.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture to egg mixture; mix well.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Lazy Daisy Frosting.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: super-crisp country fried chicken
directions: Blend Milk and Egg.
Combine Flour and seasonings until well mixed and put into a sealable container.
Place some of the flour mixture on a plate.
Roll the Chicken pieces into the four mixture until evenly coated.
Then roll into egg mixture.
Roll a second time into the flour mixture.
Deep fry in a cooker at 365 for 15 to 18 minutes.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs, shortening and molasses well. Add flour, salt, cinnamon, sugar, cloves and baking soda to creamed mixture. Chill!
Form into balls and roll in sugar. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: lemony catfish in foil
directions: Place catfish on piece of foil about 4 inches longer than fish.
Melt margarine and add the lemon juice, pepper, carrots, celery, onion and parsley.
Pour mixture over fish dividing evenly.
Top fish with lemon slices.
Bring edges of foil together and fold over several times.
Twist on the end to form a tail. Tuck other end under to form a point.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Yields 4 servings with 170 calories and 7 grams of fat.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and mix until lumps dissolve.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain off all the fat. Line a glass pie pan with the biscuits; pour the hamburger mixture over biscuits. Pour the cheese in the beaten egg. Stir and sprinkle all over pie. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are done and cheese is melted.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice (discard remaining juice or save for another use). Set the juice and pineapple aside. In a bowl, combine the egg, bread crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Shape into 40 meatballs. In a nonstick skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain. Cut green peppers into chunks. Add broth, peppers and reserved pineapple to meatballs. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes. Meanwhile, combine sugar and cornstarch in a bowl. Stir in the vinegar, soy sauce and reserved pineapple juice until smooth. Add to meatball mixture. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: chicken and broccoli pot pies
directions: Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Place each in an ungreased muffin cup.
Press dough to cover sides and bottom, forming 1/4 inch rim.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of cheese, then cereal into each cup and dot with butter.
Combine chicken, soup and broccoli.
Spoon about 1/3 cup over cereal.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce, if desired.
Can make ahead and refrigerate up to 2 hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Cook fruit sweetened to taste. Use 1/3 stick margarine in fruit. Pour fruit in dish. Mix ingredients. Crumble or drop on top of fruit until covered. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt together brown sugar and margarine.
Pour glaze in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange small pineapple slices next in the bottom of the pan.
Place maraschino cherry half in each center of pineapple.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour cake over pineapple glaze.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Check.
Turn pan upside-down on cookie sheet.
If pineapple sticks to pan when turned upside-down, lay back on cake where they should be.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw hamburg into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with soup mix.
Then spread the celery soup over all.
Layer Tater Tots close together evenly on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chinese gamble
directions: Brown meat in oil.
When meat is no longer pink, drain off fat.
Add onions, celery and soups.
Rinse each can with hot water about half full; add to meat mixture.
Simmer for a few minutes. Stir in rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Turn into a large greased casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Cover with noodles and continue to bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cinnamon candy in hot, hot water.
Add applesauce and cold water.
Pour into a mold and let set.
Unmold and serve.

title: thelma's salad
directions: Make jello by box directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drain pineapple, save juice for topping.
Add pineapple to jello; add bananas and cherries and nuts, if desired.
Put a layer of marshmallows over this.
While jello is setting, make the topping.

title: cran-cherry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts.
Chill until partially set.
Pour half gelatin mixture into a 6 1/2 cup ring mold.
Chill until almost firm.
Let remaining mixture set at room temperature.
Spread the sour cream evenly over the almost set gelatin in the mold.
Gently spoon the remaining gelatin mixture on top of sour cream layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Serves 12.

title: diabetic dinner - stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Precook green pepper shells in boiling salted water about 5 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle inside of shells generously with salt.

title: roy's favorite
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; place in bottom of casserole.
Layer potatoes and carrots on top.
Pour the green peas (drained) over top, then pour the crushed tomatoes over, juice and all.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, vanilla, oil, eggs, soda, flour, salt and warm coffee.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits, butterscotch bits, coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini tomato strata
directions: In skillet, melt butter or margarine; saute onion and garlic. Line bottom of greased, 2 qt. shallow baking dish with 3 rows saltine crackers; each row has 6 crackers slightly overlapping. Sprinkle with half cheddar, mozzarella and onion.
Top with half zucchini and 1 Tbsp. parmesan
Repeat similar layers.
Arrange tomatoes around edge; place 4 crackers in overlapping line down center.
Combine skim milk, eggs, basil and oregano.
Add to casserole; sprinkle with remaining parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: english muffins with crab or shrimp
directions: Mix all together and spread on split English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas relish
directions: Pour boiling water over first 3 ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and boil for 10 minutes.
Put into clean steamed jars and seal.
The longer it is in the jar the better it tastes.

title: peach punch
directions: Boil 2 cups water; stir in peach jello until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: punch (green)
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
At the last minute, add 1 Seven-Up.
Serves 16.

title: light as a feather yeast rolls
directions: Combine shortening, salt, sugar and dry milk; add boiling water and stir until shortening melts.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, stir into cooled first mixture.
Stir in eggs, beaten to a froth.
Stir in about 1 cup flour and blend thoroughly.
Add remaining flour and beat vigorously until batter is smooth.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Beat again. Fill greased muffin pans almost 2/3 full.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 50 minutes.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Makes 2 dozen.
Will keep a week to 10 days refrigerated.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand 1/2 hour.
Beat eggs, salt, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add apple-sugar mix alternately with flour mix to egg mix.
Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot turkey sub sandwiches
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together the olive oil and basil.
Split the French bread lengthwise.
Brush the cut surface of the top half with the olive oil mixture.
On the bottom half of the French bread, layer the turkey slices and mozzarella cheese. Wrap sandwich in foil and bake in a 350 degree oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Top sandwiches with pickles, tomatoes and lettuce.
Cut large French bread loaf into slices and serve.

title: campers' hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.
For each serving, combine 3/4 cup hot water and 1/4 cup hot chocolate mix.
Stir.
Top with marshmallow, if desired. Makes 15 cups chocolate mix.

title: raspberry mold
directions: Mix jello, cinnamon, cranberry juice and water until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold.
Chill.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt ingredients together on top of double boiler.

title: taco salad
directions: Place bite size lettuce in dish.
Mix all other ingredients and place on lettuce bed.
Garnish with tomato wedges and grated cheese.

title: hominy bake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. For crust, combine flour and sugar in medium bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is crumbly. Press lightly onto bottom and halfway up sides of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: green rice and sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine.
Pour in tin.
Sprinkle each muffin with brown sugar or cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and milk to boil and boil for four minutes. Add oleo and rest of ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 1 1/2 hours on a very low flame.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, Miracle Whip and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add flour and baking soda; set aside 1 cup of batter.
Spread remaining batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Top crust with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved batter over pecans; bake 12 to 15 minutes more, or until brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: five cup salad
directions: Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef with onion, garlic and seasonings.
Stir to separate meat.
Mix meat mixture, soup, water and noodles.
Place in 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place cheese around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Boil until thick, stirring all the time.
Place wafers and bananas in a dish.
Pour mixture over when cooled.

title: grandma l's applesauce fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce and egg, then sift dry ingredients (saving a little to coat or dust on your chopped fruit).
Then add fruit and mix. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
When removed from oven, you may rub some apple juice on top of cake.
After it cools, more apple juice may be rubbed on top of cake.

title: eye of round marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.
Marinate roast 1 to 3 days, turning once a day.
Cook, covered, in Dutch oven with marinade for 3 hours at 250°.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and serve with warm marinade.

title: eggplant a la franscine
directions: Cut eggplant in half and boil until soft.
Remove and let cool.
Remove pulp and smash it fine with fork.
In the skillet, heat oil.
Brown onion, pepper, garlic and pulp.
Mix cheese, catsup and salt.
Put mixture in the half shell eggplant. Sprinkle bread crumbs and brown under broiler.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster-spinach potage
directions: Stir milk into soup in saucepan.
Add spinach.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes over gentle heat.
Stir in wine, oysters with their liquid and pepper.
Heat well; if oysters are fresh, allow about
10 minutes.
Makes 5 cups or about 4 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, sugar, flour, salt, and nutmeg together. Add the rhubarb. Set aside. Make pie crust for bottom and top crust. Pour rhubarb mixture in to the bottom crust. Add butter. Put on top crust. Bake 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Place beans in deep bowl or pan.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread over beans.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in the bowl.
Serve with baked Tostitos.

title: peanut butter brownies(makes 24)
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat the peanut butter and butter in a large bowl with electric mixer until well blended.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy and light.
Stir in flour and salt until well blended.
Spread batter in prepared baking pan.
Bake in prepared oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 24 brownies.

title: spiced tea
directions: Shake together good; add enough hot water for 1 gallon or can be made a cup at a time at strength to your own taste.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together good and freeze in large oblong pan.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: garden salad
directions: Marinate peas, carrots, celery, green beans and onion in French dressing.
Chill for 2 hours.
Separate cauliflower flowerets and marinate separately in French dressing.
Arrange lettuce on a platter or in individual dishes; pile vegetables on lightly.
Use separated cauliflower for a border around vegetables.
Garnish with strips of red and green peppers.
Serves 6.

title: furr's pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together 2 cups powdered sugar and butter with electric mixer.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Spread mixture evenly into baked pie crusts, then chill.

title: baked orange-cardamom apples
directions: Arrange apples in circles in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Stir together honey, orange concentrate and cardamom.
Pour over apples and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated 375° oven, basting once with pan juices, 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve warm as side dish with lamb or pork or as dessert.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola icing
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans in small mixer bowl. Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Spread on cake.

title: best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Set sugar mixture aside.
Combine egg yolks, water and lemon juice; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon rind.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Spread with meringue over hot filling.
Bake pie at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 stick melted butter and 1 beaten egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1 stick softened butter, confectioners sugar and 3 beaten eggs until well mixed.
Pour on crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple sour cream cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat well. Pour into greased 13 x9-inch pan.
Top with can of apple pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curry dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix well.
Good with carrots, celery, squash, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Brown beef, add remaining ingredients with 1 soup can of water.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Quick and easy.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread evenly, then dump pie filling on top and spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix over cherry layer; spread evenly, then sprinkle chopped pecans over cake mix.
Put sliced butter over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cooled.
Good warm with ice cream!

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice unpeeled cucumbers approximately 1/4-inch thick into rectangular pan.
Sprinkle with salt; mix and let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
Place in colander and rinse with cold water; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pack cucumbers into large jars.
Pour vinegar mixture over.
Cover and store in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks before eating. Delicious!

title: hungry jack beef and beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In pan, cook hamburg and onion; drain. Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
Heat until bubbly. Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuits, cut in half. Place cut side down, over hot mixture around edge.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and confectioners sugar together. Chill for 2 hours.
Make into balls and dip in melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt cheese and margarine together. Blend broccoli and cheese mixture together.
Mix in Ritz crumbs. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs or cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and both sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and eggs.
Now add all of the flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add the M&M's; blend gently.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil water, vinegar and sugar and let cool. Place chopped ingredients and pimento in mixing bowl with lid. Mix with sauerkraut. Pour liquid over all and marinate 24 hours. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: carolyn's secret sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch rounds.
In 5-quart pot, cook beer and brown sugar together until sugar dissolves.
Add sausage and bring to boil, then turn heat down to simmer for 30 to 45 minutes. Even better if it could sit for a while after that so sausage can absorb the flavor.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Will be moist.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat well together.
Keeps in fridge many months.
Will not separate.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook the apple juice concentrate and the tapioca until thick. Add apples to the hot mixture; stir until well coated.
Spoon into pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add the top crust.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Break brownies and Heath bars into pieces.
Put ingredients into a deep dish as follows:
Spread brownie pieces on bottom. Add a layer of instant chocolate mousse.
Add a layer of Heath bar pieces.
Cover with layer of whipped topping.
Repeat layers.

title: brown sugar baked apples
directions: Core apples, being sure not to cut all the way through.
Cut a thin slice from top of each.
Place apples on microwavesafe pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn once.
Meanwhile, mix sugar, water, flour and cinnamon in small bowl until smooth.
Spoon evenly over apples; dot with butter.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes until sauce is bubbly and apples are barely tender.
Let stand 3 minutes until tender.
Spoon sauce from pie plate over apples.

title: mexi-beef bites
directions: Cook beef until pink is gone, drain.
Stir in cheeses, chilies, taco sauce, jalapeno pepper and eggs.
Transfer mixture to an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean and top is golden brown. Serve warm.
Spoon onto individual plates and eat with tortilla chips.

title: divinity pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat sugar in egg whites.
Roll Ritz crackers fine.
Add to egg mixture with pecans, chopped fine. Butter pie plate, pour mixture into plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let it get cold and put Dream Whip, made by recipe, and add confectioners sugar and instant cocoa on top and put in refrigerator.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Turn into a baking dish.
Top with uncooked bacon and olives. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a large buttered casserole dish, place the cooked egg noodles.
Brown the hamburger in a skillet.
Saute the onion and green pepper in the hamburger.
Drain the fat, then add the meat on top of the noodles.
Use garlic salt and pepper to taste. Combine the tomatoes, soup and taco seasoning and pour on top of meat.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Mix, then add strawberries. After these are mixed well, add rest of ingredients and pour in container and chill.
Add topping.

title: kentucky fried chicken taste alike
directions: Wash and dry your chicken, then apply twice to each piece of chicken.
It will be ready to bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or deep fry.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the pineapple tidbits, Mandarin oranges, coconut and cherries. Stir the apple into the sour cream, and add to the fruit mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Stir before serving.

title: butter crust parfait pie
directions: Combine butter with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Do not cream.
Add flour.
Mix just until a dough will form.
Place 1/4 to 1/3 of this mixture in a small pan.
Press remaining mixture evenly over bottom and side of a 9-inch pie pan with well floured fingers. Bake at 375° until light golden brown (crust: 12 to 15 minutes or crumbs: 10 to 12 minutes).

title: farmhouse breakfast muffins
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain. Add beaten eggs; stir well. Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Flatten into small circles. Press each into bottom and sides of a greased muffin pan. Divide the meat mixture among biscuits, using about 1/4 cup for each. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan. Good to make a day ahead and keep refrigerated, then pop in microwave to reheat.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Microwave on Low for 5 minutes or oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: roast pork loin with mustard herb coating
directions: Combine Dijon mustard, minced garlic, olive oil, balsamic vinegar and rosemary in small bowl; whisk to blend.
Dry pork with paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread mustard mixture all over pork.
Place bay leaves on top of roast.
Marinate for several hours, if possible.

title: minute steak
directions: *Sometimes I just use whole can of mushroom soup and no celery soup.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add water and liquid shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Before removing, drizzle with glaze made of confectioners sugar, lemon juice and butter.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream.
Add to meat with rest of ingredients, all but sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls the size of a walnut.
Saute all sides in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Remove balls and make sauce from drippings.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds from cucumbers.
Cut into strips.
Mix 2 cups lime and 8 quarts of water.
Put cucumbers in mixture to soak 24 hours.
Drain and wash in cold water.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute onion in shortening until tender. Combine egg and milk; add to Bisquick and stir until blended.
Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased round glass baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice.
Combine chicken and cooked rice.
Add onion, pimento and beans.
Combine mayonnaise and soup.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes in 2-quart casserole until bubbly and brown.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together sugar, pecans and butter.	Put in 9 x 13 pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Beat cream cheese and sugar; add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crumb crust.
Mix pudding and milk together; pour over cream cheese mixture.	Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain and repeat, rinsing and draining.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Combine with macaroni, celery, onion, carrots and pepper.

title: orange chiffon cake(large)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a large well and add oil, egg yolks, juice from oranges and orange rind.
Mix well until smooth.
Measure into large bowl the egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat until eggs form a very stiff peak; do not underbeat.
Gently fold egg yolk mixture into whipped egg whites just until blended.
Do not stir.
Pour into ungreased pan immediately.
Cut through batter with knife to remove air bubbles.
In 10 x 4-inch tube or angel food pan bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch oblong bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top springs back lightly.
Turn pan upside down until cool.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.
Frost with Orange Icing.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a real hard ball in cold water.
While it is cooking, beat the egg whites.
After syrup forms a hard ball, pour over the beaten egg whites and beat until it comes to a peak to be handled.
Then pour out on a powdered sugar dough board.
Fold over a time or two, then divide it into 3 parts for easier handling.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, vanilla and vinegar. Stir and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use an 8 or 9-inch square dish.

title: peanut butter spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar/butter mixture, beating well after each addition.
Dough will be stiff.
Put in spritz maker.
Press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden around the edges.
Do not overbake.
Makes 14 to 16 dozen cookies. Very crispy.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites stiff, then fold into mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan or a Bundt pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Cream remaining 1 cup butter with remaining 2 cups sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla; mix well. Combine 2 3/4 cups flour with the baking powder and salt. Gradually add to the creamed mixture, beating until well blended. Dredge blueberries with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Stir to coat well.
Fold the blueberry and flour mixture into the batter.

title: warren and lib's tuna pate
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in tuna until well blended. Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Grate carrots.
Chop onion and bell pepper. Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Makes one gallon of salad.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and seasoning mix together.
Spread over beans.
Spread guacamole over sour cream.
Chop onions and spread over top with black olives and tomatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.

title: tuna pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Combine rotini, broccoli, tomatoes, olives, onion and tuna; set aside.
Combine vinegar, lemon juice, water, olive oil, mustard and pepper in a jar.
Cover tightly; shake vigorously. Pour over pasta mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Toss gently before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Mix with rest of ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into oiled Pyrex dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-potato bake
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes with margarine, salt and milk. Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain well. Fold into mashed potatoes. Put into lightly greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 4 cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over heat until it reaches the hard ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and beat in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour mixture over corn and mix well. Bake at 225° for about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove and let cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Partially cook and drain limas and broccoli.
Mix all together and put into baking dish.
Mix 1/4 cup of melted butter with 3 cups cereal (Rice Krispies or corn flakes).
Use for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat at 325° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: sausage and cabbage soup
directions: Cook onion, carrots, celery and garlic in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add cabbage, water and bouillon granules.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Add sausage, tomatoes with juice and pepper to mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot shrimp dip with pita chips
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir flour and sugar in medium bowl until well
blended.
Whisk
in melted butter until thoroughly combined. Whisk
in
eggs until thoroughly blended.
Whisk in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour
mixture into pie crust and bake 1 hour, or until
filling
is
golden
brown
and sharp knife inserted in center of filling is withdrawn clean.

title: mini focaccia rounds
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Remove dough from can.
Separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks.
Place coils on greased cookie sheets.
Press each coil into a 4-inch circle.
Drizzle with olive oil.
In small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese, rosemary, basil and onion. Sprinkle over dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aroma punch
directions: Place the orange and lemon peel in a small pan. Add the cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Pour the water over the fruit and spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat until the liquid is at a low boil.

title: easy san francisco stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef; cook and stir until no longer pink.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Bring carrots and butter to a boil. Stir in brown sugar; cover and simmer for approximately 40 minutes. Cooking time may vary depending on thickness of carrot slices.

title: joanne's potato salad(serves 8)
directions: Peel and cut up red potatoes.
Peel and chop eggs.
Add red onion, parsley, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Squeeze lemon and pour juice on salad.
Slowly drizzle salad oil over salad.
Stir in as much Best Foods mayonnaise as is needed.
Refrigerate

title: hearty beef and vegetable stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add beef and shake until coated.
In large pot or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add meat in batches and cook until browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove meat. Reduce heat to medium.
Add onion, garlic and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.

title: strawberry mango ice cream
directions: Puree the mango in blender or food processor.
This should make about 1/2 cup mango puree.
Combine the mango with the strawberries and set aside.
Heat the 2 c. milk in the microwave or in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in the half & half and then add vanilla extract.
Pour into freezer canister and add enough milk to fill. Freeze according to directions given with your freezer.

title: nestle holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: apple puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Beat.
Add apples and stir.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels for 3 to 5 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar.
Makes 10 to 15.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine 2 tablespoons butter, cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, 1 egg, 3 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat at high speed until smooth and creamy. Combine remaining ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend well. Spread 1/2 batter into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over batter.
Carefully spread other 1/2 of batter over the cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes but make first check at 40 minutes.

title: simple chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken with grapes; add mayonnaise.
Before serving, stir in 1/2 cup toasted almonds.

title: egg corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add milk and egg.
Melt shortening and pour in last.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy cheeseroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; brown ground beef and drain.
Add soups, green pepper and cooked macaroni. Place half the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with half the cheese and onions.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Combine popcorn and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, heat oil.
Stir sugar into hot oil.
Add popcorn and water mixture; cover.
Pop the corn quickly over high heat, shaking pan constantly.
At the end of the peak of popcorn popping, remove pan from heat to prevent sugar from burning. Makes about 6 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well; chill and serve with crackers.

title: cabbage-hamburger casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in 3 teaspoons butter.
Add ground beef, seasoned to taste, and saute.
Put a layer of cabbage in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with a layer of beef.
Top with the rest of the cabbage.
Pour a can of tomato soup over all.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding as directed on the box.
Let sit for 5 minutes in the refrigerator.
Thaw the Cool Whip.
Mix the pudding with the Cool Whip and then refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Lay the wafers on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 3 sliced bananas and half of the pudding mixture on top. Repeat.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Use a double unbaked pie crust.
Heat apple juice and cinnamon in a large saucepan. Add apple slices and cook until slices are tender.
Remove apple slices from juice and set aside.
Mix cornstarch and cold water until smooth.
Add the mixture to the apple juice and stir until thickened.
Combine apples and sauce. Cool slightly. Fill unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Add top pie crust.
Seal around edge with cold water.
Make vent holes in top crust. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Then add 1 c. milk, 1/4 c. butter, 1/2 c. sugar to pan and stir in thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, then lower heat and cook till, desired pudding like consistency, stirring often.
4 to 6 servings.

title: deer chili
directions: Cook meat, garlic and onions.
Add rest of ingredients; cook, then simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: potato bacon salad
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and put in large bowl.
Cut into bite size pieces.
In measuring cup, whisk oil and vinegar and add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and toss.
Let sit for 30 minutes and add bacon, eggs, onion, scallions and relish.
Toss gently until well mixed.
Chill covered.
Serves 4.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and flour.
Add egg and peaches. Peaches may be fresh or canned.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Put beef broth, beef, salt, peppercorns and bay leaf in 2 quarts of water.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add vegetables, bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until vegetables and meat are tender. Serves 4.

title: john marzetti
directions: Cook noodles 10 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Brown meat; add onion and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix together all ingredients except 1 cup cheese.
Place in casserole; bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with reserved cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese and brown slightly.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Combine in saucepan the eggs (beaten), cornstarch, sugar and 1 cup of juice reserved from fruit.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Cool completely.
Fold in whipping cream, nuts and marshmallows.
Add pineapple and fruit cocktail. Combine in a bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Drain and chop cherries, reserving juice. Combine flour, soda and salt. Set aside. In large mixer bowl, cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Beat well after each addition. Lightly flour cherries and pecans. Fold in mixture just until coated. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: ham glaze
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to a boil.
Spoon over baked ham during last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo and press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake mix base. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar.
To this add chilled whipped milk, fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the wafer crumbs on bottom of dish.
Pour in Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs over top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes, cream, butter and salt to taste.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup and milk.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Pour mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Make a layer of corn and layer of cheese.
Top with cream potatoes.
Bake at 400° until bubbly hot, for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Mix margarine and flour in sauce pan. Cook briefly over medium heat. Then blend in the chicken broth, stirring constantly until smooth. Stir in mushrooms and liquid. Season to taste.

Place the broccoli in a shallow pan. Cover with sliced or cut up chicken pieces. Pour mushroom sauce over all. Top with parsley and bread crumbs. Bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 15-25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add lemon juice and stir thoroughly, beating constantly and continue beating until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients. Set aside.
Mix together last 7 ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush Ritz crackers into crumbs.
Melt 1/2 stick to 1 whole stick margarine.
In casserole dish, layer crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Next, layer asparagus, both cheeses and cream of mushroom soup (these layers do not have to be in any particular order).
Repeat layers, ending with Ritz cracker crumbs, drizzled with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut ribs into six pieces and brown on all sides.
Place meaty side up in Dutch oven.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Bake uncovered on lower rack of 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Stir sauce in bottom of pan and pour over ribs and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Measure peanut butter and corn syrup in a mixing bowl.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
With back of tablespoon, press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Chill until firm.
Spread ice cream evenly in chilled crust.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, sprinkle chopped peanuts on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old-fashion lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon juice and cold water; mix well.
Yield:
7 1/4 cups.

title: special strawberry salad
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate until quite thick and put on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly until thick and smooth.
Add butter and cool.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling.
Add gelatin and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet and pour in ginger ale.
Yields 6 1/2 quarts.

title: raisin boston browned bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (1-pound) coffee cans and cut aluminum foil, 2 inches larger than opening of can, to use as lids.
Grease foil.

title: sweet sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and white sugar until dissolved and cool.
Then pour over remaining ingredients.

title: macaroni and tomato
directions: Cook macaroni and onion for 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Brown hamburger (optional) and add to macaroni; cook another 5 minutes.

title: cajun sauce-piquant
directions: Follow the basic Crawfish Etouffee
(a la blanc) recipe which can be cut in half or thirds to do peppers.
Add tomato sauce (if you haven't yet), additional red pepper to taste, raw eggs and fresh bread crumbs; mix well with hands, smashing until thick and firm enough to stuff in pepper.
Batter with egg batter and roll in flour.
Bake until browned or deep fry until browned.
Can also roll in cornmeal, if desired.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Mix potato flakes and hot water until all potatoes are mixed, but is very stiff.
May add more water, if needed.
Mix salad dressing, mustard, relish and onions; mix well.
Add eggs, salt and pepper; stir well.
May garnish with egg slices and paprika.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until the size of peas.
Add milk all at once.
Stir with fork.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased pan at 450° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: john the wop
directions: Precook noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain browned ground meat. Mix soup and sauce together.
Layer the noodles, ground meat and cheese in layers, topping with noodles and cheese.
Add soup and sauce mixture, working it through mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and add Worcestershire sauce, pepper, garlic salt and regular salt.
Mix well and add pecans.
Stir until pecans are well coated.
Spread in a shallow pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; stir and turn.
Bake for 10 minutes more.
Drain on a brown paper sack.
Store in an airtight container.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Then add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk.
Mix in coconut and nuts.
Pour in well-greased and floured stem pan and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cover cranberries with water and boil until all husks are broken.
Add sugar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, grapes, celery, pineapple and pecans.
Stir until well mixed and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: nutty cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix together cheese and butter. Add flour, nuts and 2 tablespoons cold water. Mix until mixture comes together to make a dough. Break off walnut size pieces and roll into long thin sausage shapes, about 5-inches long. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Brush with egg and bake for a further 6 to 8 minutes, until golden brown. Serve with soup. Makes 24.

title: super spud casserole
directions: Place hash browns in baking dish.
Mix together potato soup, sour cream and 8 ounces Cheddar cheese; put on top of hash browns and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, cheese, onion, carrot and soup.
Fold in zucchini and top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sliven pork chops(romania)
directions: Season pork chops and brown in skillet, then set aside.
Cook all remaining ingredients together in a skillet for 10-15 minutes until tender.
Arrange pork chops in an oven dish and cover with the vegetable mix.
Bake at 325F for 20 minutes.
Serves well with mashed or boiled potatoes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle vegetables with sugar, placing alternately in a bowl. Pour dressing over cabbage.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain shells according to package directions. Brown ground beef and onion. Stir in Parmesan cheese and 3/4 of the Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Stuff meat mixture into shells. Lightly grease pan and layer bottom with 1 jar spaghetti sauce. Place stuffed shells in pan and sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top of shells. Pour the second jar of spaghetti sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Layer noodles with mixture, first on bottom, center and a few sprinkled on top of greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter and slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix broth, mushroom soup, mixed vegetables, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Mix flour, butter and milk.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate fruit patties
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together over low heat.
Beat in sugar and cool.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to chocolate mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner following basic directions, brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix 3/4 c of water to meat. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir sour cream into prepared macaroni dinner. Spoon half of the dinner mixture, 1 c of cheese and remaining dinner mixture.
Cover and bake at 400 for 15 minutes.
Top with salsa and remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered an additional 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put in 4 cup measuring cup in order the sugar, syrup and peanuts.
Do not mix.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir.
Return to microwave and cook another 4 minutes.
Remove and add vanilla and oleo.
Stir.
Return to microwave; cook 2 minutes on High.
Remove and add baking soda. Mix quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Spread thinly. Let cool and break up.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in large dish.
Slice onion and place on top of pork chops.
Mix together rice, soup and water.
Pour this mixture over pork chops and onion.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Additional water should be added as needed to keep rice moist.

title: harold's chicken casserole
directions: Put layer of crushed crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. This is 1 package. Mix all other ingredients and put on top of bottom layer of crackers. Put rest of crackers, the 2nd package of crackers, on top and bake at 325° until bubbly and brown.

title: cheddar-chicken "muffins"
directions: Spray muffin tins to coat.
Combine ingredients and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375° or until firm and golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Season potatoes.
Mix chopped onion and potato slices.
Wrap in foil and place on grill.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes (or until soft) while cooking your meat.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of potatoes when done.
Serve hot.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese in a bowl with a wooden spoon to soften and smooth. Crumble bacon and mix with cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place on wax paper and harden in refrigerator.
When firm, roll into ball and cover with finely ground nuts.

title: light 'n fruity strawberry pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups. Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened. Remove any unmelted ice. Blend in Cool Whip; then whip until smooth. Fold in strawberries and chill until mixture will mold. Spoon into pie crust. Chill 2 hours.

title: souper mac and cheese
directions: Blend butter with macaroni.
Stir in soup, water, onion and 3/4 cup cheese.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: munch cake(cheese cake brownies)
directions: Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add frozen berries.
Chill until it begins to get solid.
Add pineapple, nuts and mix well. Put 1/2 of the mixture into 8-inch square pan and chill.
Fold whipped cream into remaining mixture and pour on top of the first jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken until tender in pan of water.
Reserve liquid to cook noodles.
Saute onions and chicken together in cooking oil. Cook noodles, onions and 1 cup cheese.
Add soups and mix together. Layer in long baking dish.
Put cheese between first and second layers.
Top with cheese.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° until it will not shake in the middle.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add mashed bananas. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Use a hand mixer for this recipe.
Allow time for cheese and butter to soften.
Cream together cheese and butter, then gradually add flour and mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator for about an hour.
Dust hands with flour and roll dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press pecan half in center of each cheese ball.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°. Do not brown.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: banana pudding(no cook)
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Whip until thick. Add condensed milk.
Whip again.
Add Cool Whip and fold in. Layer pudding mixture, vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together remaining ingredients.
Combine both mixtures.
Gradually add 2 cups peeled and grated zucchini, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and 1/2 cup butterscotch chips or raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Frosting if desired.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Remove crusts and butter bread slices.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Set aside. Brown sausage, drain and crumble.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Next, beat eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour over sausage mixture and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until set.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates (or raisins) and chopped cherries.

title: frosted cake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.

Fold the sour cream, chocolate chips and walnuts into batter. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick near the center comes out clean. Cool completely on a wire rack. Frost. Cut into bars. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until blended.
Line muffin pans with foil cupcake liners.
Put 1 vanilla wafer cookie, flat side down, in each.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture in each.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Put 2 tablespoons of pie filling on top.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper and pound lightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, combine wine, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Brush chicken on all sides with mustard mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
In a large skillet over medium heat, heat margarine and oil.
Brown chicken on both sides until fully cooked.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease 1 (9-inch) spring-form pan; dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Sieve cottage cheese into large mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese.
Beat on high speed until blended.
Then add sugar and eggs.
Blend on low speed and add starch, lemon and vanilla.
Add margarine and sour cream.
Blend on low speed and pour into pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until firm around edges.
Turn off oven and let cake stand 2 hours. Makes about 12 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place half of the potato slices in glass 8 1/2 x 13 casserole dish. Next, put half of the Velveeta slices on top of the potatoes, followed by half of the onion slices. Place half of the butter pats on top of the onion slices. Salt and pepper and sprinkle with parsley flakes. Repeat with the remaining ingredients. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: steak pizziole
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Transfer meat in a deep baking pan.
Add green olives with juice.
Add chopped onion around meat, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour crushed tomato on top of meat.
Add olive oil on top of everything (about 1/4 cup).
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 1 1/2 hour or until tender.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large Tupperware Fix-N-Mix bowl.
Pour oil over oyster crackers.
Put on Tupperware seal and flip well.
Mix all seasonings together and sprinkle over crackers.
Mix well and eat!

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes longer. Cool and refrigerate.

title: nonalcoholic eggnog(recipe for diabetic)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Pour into cups and serve.
Yield: 4 cups.
Exchanges per 1 cup serving: 1/3 skim milk, 1/2 meat and 62 calories.

title: two, three, four pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add enough flour to make dough easy to handle, but not stiff.
Transfer to pastry board.
Press out dough and fold over several times.
(This makes crust flaky.) Add a little flour as needed to keep dough from sticking to board. Roll out and cover pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly browned.
Before baking, pierce dough with fork.

title: wienees in a wrap
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Unroll crescent dough.
Pinch crescent dough together at seams to form a square.
Turn square to form a diamond.
Place one slice of cheese in middle of diamond.
Put wienee at one end of dough and roll.
Place seam side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried pork tenderloin
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Cut tenderloin crosswise into 1/8-inch thick slices.
In medium-size bowl, mix pork with next 5 ingredients.

In a 12-inch skillet or wok over high heat, in 3 tablespoons of salad oil, cook broccoli, mushrooms, carrot and salt, stirring quickly and frequently (stir-frying) until vegetables are coated with oil.
Add water and stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp; spoon onto warm platter.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix well all of ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: cereal snacks
directions: Mix dressing mix with oil.
Drizzle alternately oil and dressing mix.
Shake spice mix while stirring.
Place in 250° oven to finish drying and crisping.

title: mom's english toffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Cream butter and sugar until smooth. Add egg yolk and mix. Add flour and cinnamon and mix thoroughly. Spread in an even layer over entire surface of a greased cookie sheet with sides. Beat egg white slightly and spread over top. Sprinkle pecans evenly over top and lightly pat into dough. Bake at 275° for 1 hour until lightly browned. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: nana's fig bars
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut into square like brownies.

title: egg glop
directions: Soak onion soup in milk; set aside.
Cook well in electric skillet the hash browns and Canadian bacon in butter.
Add softened onion soup mixture and beaten eggs.
Stir gently; lower heat setting to 125° and cover until set, approximately 20 minutes.
When set, cover with cheese; cover another 5 minutes until completely melted.
Serve.

title: peppered beef brisket
directions: Push black pepper into both sides of flank steak; mix marinade and pour over meat in a Ziploc bag.
(I marinate meat at least overnight in refrigerator before cooking.)

title: grandmother naomi's butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix and roll into two logs.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together to make a dough.
Place 1/2 of mixture between 2 pieces of wax paper and roll out or dough can be pressed into a pie plate by hand.
Follow favorite pie recipe for filling.

title: mexican food
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add chopped garlic, chopped green chilies, jalapeno peppers and chopped onion; simmer 5 minutes.
Crush Doritos and spread in bottom of large baking pan.
Mix 3/4 of grated cheese, picante sauce, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour ground beef mixture in over Doritos; pour soup mixture over beef and sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: tuna fish mousse
directions: Mince tuna.
Whip cream.
Dilute gelatine in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Allow to cool, then mix with tuna and cream.
Add seasonings. Pour into mold.
Allow time to set in refrigerator.

title: chicken parmesan with gravy
directions: Dip chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour or less at 350°.
Turn up to broil for 2 to 3 minutes to brown.
Remove chicken.
Pour broth into pan; stir to loosen particles.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Cook 5 minutes.
Use as chicken gravy.

title: dandy rock candy
directions: You will need a quart-size cooking pot, blue food coloring, a pint-size canning jar, string and a pencil.

title: mary pickford cookies
directions: Mix and roll 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with filling.

title: georgia's chicken(easy and elegant)
directions: Pour sauce over chicken.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat the eggs, then combine the margarine, eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over 1/2 to 3/4 cup raisins; let set 5 minutes and drain.
Add the coarsely chopped pecans, coconut and drained raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt butter. Mix with graham crackers. Mix dream whip according to package directions. Mix together cream cheese and sugar; add to dream whip, put graham cracker mixture on bottom of 8 inch dish saving 1/4 cup for top. Add 1/2 dream whip mixture. Spread cherry pie filling over. Top with remaining dream whip. Sprinkle graham cracker on top.

title: laura's worry free ice cream
directions: Cream sugars and egg substitute until smooth.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla and mix well.
Add nonfat milk and pour into freezer container.
If larger than 5-quart freezer is used, add additional nonfat milk as required.
May be topped with fresh fruit of your choice.
This recipe was created for and tested by my family with a low fat, low sugar content.
At last we can enjoy homemade ice cream frequently and guilt free.

title: honey-peanut squares
directions: Bring sugar and honey to a boil in a saucepan (1-quart). Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and stir until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture over previously combined Cheerios and nuts. Stir until well coated.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press down.
Cool and cut.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Knead about 5 times on floured board/cloth with Pioneer buttermilk baking mix until mixture is no longer sticky.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness (or more if you want higher biscuits) and cut out biscuits.
Place on small baking sheet (I use 9 1/2-inch wide by 11 1/2-inches long) close together.
Please Note:
Line the baking sheet with aluminum foil; spray with butter Pam.
After placing all biscuits on pan, spray top of each biscuit with butter Pam.
