Bake in 450° preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 12.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on the cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours and then drain.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes. Bottle while hot.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep tea bags for 5 minutes in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour over sugar.
Dissolve lemonade and orange concentrate.
Pour in bourbon and water and freeze.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fachi di vechia
directions: Pat part of the
homemade
bread (dough recipe follows) out about 1 inch thick onto
a
large
cookie sheet with sides which has been well oiled
with
olive
oil.
Push
some holes down in the dough so topping will sink into dough as it bakes. Let dough rise in warm
place
until
double
in
size, 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350°
for
to
35 minutes.
(Note:
Frozen loaves of bread may be used.)

title: ham dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: christmas casserole cookies
directions: In a 2-quart greased casserole, combine eggs and sugar, mixing well.
Add coconut, vanilla, dates, nuts (optional) and almond extract.
Stir together real good.
Bake in a 350 ° oven for 30 minutes or 10 to 12 minutes in microwave.
Stir every 3 minutes. Remove from oven; stir with a wooden spoon while hot.
While still warm, make balls and roll in granulated sugar or coconut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Also good on toast.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Unroll dough.
Separate into triangles.
Put pizza sauce, mozzarella cheese, and pepperoni on triangles.
Place another triangle on top and pinch together.
Bake at 375 for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together caramels, butter, milk, chocolate chips and nuts. Pour half of cake batter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Pour caramel mixture over half-baked cake.
Pour remaining cake batter over caramel. Add chocolate chips and nuts on top. Bake 30 more minutes until done.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken in skillet on medium heat 10 minutes.
Brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Simmer 10 minutes on low heat or until tender and broccoli is done.
Cook 25 minutes.

title: pea and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook peas and broccoli.
Drain and save water.
Add soup and cheese to the water.
Cook until melted.
Pour over vegetables. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process until well blended.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar.
Put into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: flapper pudding
directions: Take 12 whole months.
Clean them thoroughly of all bitterness, hate and jealousy.
Make them fresh and clean as possible. Cut each month into 28, 30 or 31 different parts. Prepare it one day at a time.
Mix well into each day.

title: chocolate and oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter in bowl.
Mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup and press remaining oat mixture on bottom of 9 X 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour condensed milk on evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Top with remaining oat mixture.
Press down.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball or can be made into a loaf.
Chopped pecans can be put on for a more decorative effect or flavor.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Mash bananas with mixer and combine with juices. Combine sugar and water and boil 5 minutes. Add to banana mixture. Divide into 3 half gallon containers and freeze. 2 hrs before servings, remove from freezer. To serve, add sprite or ginger ale and mix well with juice.

title: lime cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, add milk, lime juice and vanilla, beating until smooth. Pour into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours. Spread with whipped topping and refrigerate 1 hour longer. 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and put in dish.
Sprinkle coconut over top and chill.

title: leah's mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix everything together except nuts.
When all ingredients are mixed well, add nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Pour frosting on hot cake.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Bottom	Crust:	Mix flour, oleo and nuts together.
Pat in a pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, measure rice, water and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer and cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Place cooked rice in the top of a double boiler; stir in condensed milk and butter.
Cook in double boiler until mixture has thickened, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and raisins.
Spoon into parfait glasses, alternating with pie filling.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: cream pies
directions: Note:
I substitute 3 rounded tablespoonfuls of cornstarch instead of flour.

title: tamale stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green peppers lengthwise.
Wash, put in water and boil until tender.
Into a heavy skillet, put 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add finely chopped onion; cook until tender.
Add ground meat and minced garlic.
Brown meat.
Add salt and chili powder; stir well.
Add 1 cup water from boiled peppers and the minced tomatoes.
Let simmer with top on until meat is tender and most all liquid gone.
Add cornmeal slowly, stirring constantly. When thick enough to hold in place, mold and fill peppers on baking dish.
Put remainder of mixture around peppers.
Bake at 450° until almost dry.

title: chicken mole
directions: In a pan of boiling water, add the chicken breast with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and shred. In a frying pan, heat shortening; add garlic and brown slightly. Add flour and stir until well blended.
Gradually stir in chili powder.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add shredded chicken breast and cook 3 to 5 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Place strawberries, sugar and 1 cup water in medium size pot and cook 5 minutes on medium, then turn setting down to low and cook for another 5 minutes.
Remove strawberries and allow to cool.
Slice pound cake into 1/2 in sections.
After the pound cake has been sliced into sections, be sure there is enough for 2 layers.
Place 1 layer of cake in a flat serving pan or bowl. Spread a moderate amount of strawberries over the first layer of cake and half cup of juices from the cooked strawberries.
Add a layer of Cool Whip topping to the first layer of cake and strawberries.
Place another layer of pound cake on top of Cool Whip and add strawberries, juices and Cool Whip.
After everything is finished, there should be 2 layers of cake, Cool Whip and strawberries.
The amount of each ingredient used will determine how many servings are made.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Top of cookies will look pale.)
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix milk and Tang.
Add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread into pie crust.
Decorate the top with mandarin oranges or sliced kiwi fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: butter baked carrot sticks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Butter a shallow baking dish.
Scrape or peel carrots and cut into sticks about 2 inches long.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt, pepper and dill.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover (use foil if pan has no cover).
Bake about 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Add sugar slowly to margarine in a large bowl, beating well.
Beat in one egg until smooth.
Add other egg and beat well.
Add half the flour mixture, half the milk and the vanilla.
Mix.
Add rest of flour mixture and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Fill a greased and floured baking pan or 2 layer pans no more than half full.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched near center.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Lightly oil 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add rice to dish. Place chicken on top of rice and sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour on 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 2 soup cans of water.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water; drain and reserve chicken stock. Bone and dice chicken.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter; add Velveeta and melt.
Blend in soup, mushrooms and olives.
Add chicken and 1 cup of reserved stock.
Boil noodles in remaining stock until done; add to chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a large casserole dish.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into baking dish. Spread ketchup over top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato dish
directions: Grate boiled potatoes into a greased baking dish
Place on top fried onions and a layer of sour cream.
Add a layer of grated potatoes and layer of grated mild Longhorn cheese.
Add a layer of potatoes, topped with Parmesan cheese and bake until heated through at 350°.

title: frosted applesauce cake
directions: Combine applesauce, butter, brown sugar and raisins in saucepan.
Heat until butter and sugar dissolves; let stand until cool.
Sift spices, salt, flour and soda together; stir into applesauce mixture.
Add nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup of sugar, oil and sour cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour half of batter in a well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: japanese salad dressing
directions: Put in blender, then chill.
Serve on salad.

title: trifle dessert
directions: Cube angel food cake.
Mix jello and water until dissolved. Drop frozen strawberries in hot jello (will gel quickly).
Prepare instant pudding.
Alternate all ingredients in layers in trifle bowl: jello, strawberries, cake, pudding; repeat layers.
Decorate top layer with Cool Whip, kiwi, bananas and mandarin oranges.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas to above mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping, blending well.
Add strawberries and spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before cutting; keep chilled in refrigerator.
Garnish with additional berries. Store any leftover pie in freezer.
Serves 6.

title: yogurt cups
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar until crumbly; sprinkle in water, 1 teaspoon at a time, stirring until dough forms.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add vanilla, milk, nutmeg, salt, flour and sugar; add rhubarb and mix well. Pour into deep-dish pie shell. Mix topping ingredients and sprinkle over pie. Bake at 450° for 7 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake until golden brown.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown onions and celery in the fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Serve on buns or other rolls.
Good with potato salad or chips.

title: mother's flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening.
Pour in hot water and
mix
to
a
stiff dough.
Knead on slightly floured breadboard	until
soft
and pliable.
Cover dough with mixing bowl and allow to rest for about 30 minutes.
Preheat griddle. Form
dough balls into biscuit-sized balls.
Roll out thin and bake
on
ungreased
griddle.
Turn
tortillas
when
top side begins to show some puffiness or blisters.	Turn to other side and cook until lightly brown.
Keep covered in bread basket.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: easiest to work with roll out sugar cookies
directions: Mix above and split into 3 balls and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Dip fish fillets in batter, then coat with crumbs.
Have 1/2-inch hot oil ready.
Fry fish and drain on paper towels.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Blend in one medium whole egg.
Sift together and add to the salt, baking powder and flour. Blend into mixture 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice and apple juice into crock-pot.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Tie cinnamon sticks and cloves in cheesecloth and place into pot. Cover and simmer on high for 2 hours.
Remove spice bag.
Serve warm.

title: southwest casserole
directions: *May substitute 2 (15-ounce) cans Progresso black beans, drained.

title: my favorite coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Leave cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, put the can of coconut oil on cake.
I punch holes before putting on the coconut oil.
Let cool.
Spread with Cool Whip, then your frozen coconut.

title: ultimate cookies(saye noguchi)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Stir in oil, egg and vanilla. Add cereal. Sift flour and baking powder into butter and sugar mixture.
Stir to combine. Add oats, coconut, nuts and chocolate chips. Stir well.
Place heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten top slightly with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned in a 325° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: seafood special
directions: Combine crabmeat and next 10 ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan
or
in
6 individual baking dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile saute shrimp, scallops, green onion and mushroom in butter.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place on top of baked
crab
crust.
Top with cheese sauce.
Return to hot oven 5 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: MIx all ingredients and put in greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 inch or layers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry-fresh pie
directions: Combine pie mix, Jell-O, water and lemon juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool.
Prepare Dream Whip. Fold 1 1/2 cups into cooled Jell-O mix.
Blend well. Add berries and pour
into baked (cool) pie shell (9-inch).
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Garnish with the 1/2 cup Dream Whip.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Grease a baking dish with butter.
Spread with rice.
Smooth soup over rice and pour over 1 1/4 cans water. Top with chicken, salted and peppered, skin side up. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: goulash texas style
directions: Saute hamburger meat and drain.
Add the bell pepper and onion and saute a little.
Add all other ingredients and about 3 cups water and simmer until noodles are done.
Don't make this dish too thick.
Serve with corn bread and green salad.

title: do-nothing cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt, eggs and vanilla in mixer bowl; mix well.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour frosting over hot cake.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: hash brown omelet
directions: Cut 6 bacon slices into 1-inch pieces.
Pan fry until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.

title: cheese-tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook noodles; drain and set aside.

title: sante fe soup
directions: Simmer 30 minutes. Can be made ahead of time.

title: robust bean soup
directions: Wash the dried beans and then place in soup pot with water to cover.
Allow to soak overnight or several hours.
Pour off water and cover once again with water.
Cook until beans are almost tender.
Add ham flavor packet, Essence seasoning, onion, bell pepper, smoked sausage, Rotel, and diced tomatoes.
Cook over medium heat until onions and bell pepper are tender.
Add butter and Tabasco. Taste and add salt and black pepper, as needed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Drain well and crumble.
Put cut broccoli flowerets, chopped onion and raisins in large mixing bowl. Add mayonnaise and toss lightly.
Garnish with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine onion, celery, potatoes and salt.
Add water, just enough to cover potatoes.
When potatoes are almost done, mash all ingredients.
Add milk, sour cream, margarine and parsley until thickened.

title: vegetable salad deluxe
directions: Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces. (You can buy packages of broccoli and cauliflower that have already been prepared.)
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix together and set aside.
Add water chestnuts, peas, corn, onion, bacon bits and cheese to broccoli and cauliflower.
Gently mix all ingredients, slowly stirring in the mayonnaise mixture. Refrigerate until ready to eat (at least 2 hours).

title: chocolate delight
directions: Take 1 cup walnuts, 1 cup flour and 1 stick melted oleo. Blend together and press in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and set aside.

title: artichoke bisque
directions: Chop 2 artichoke hearts, set aside.
Place remaining artichokes in food processor, puree.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat, add flour, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stir occasionally.
Gradually add milk, water, bouillon granules and lemon juice, stir occasionally.
Add reserved artichokes and pureed artichokes.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stir occasionally for 10 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Garnish each serving with a lemon twist.

title: quick and tasty barbecues
directions: Brown and drain meat and onion.
Add pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: phyllis' waffles
directions: Beat egg whites.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
To dry mixture add egg yolks, milk, oil and beaten egg whites.
Cook until golden brown.

title: veg-all chicken pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Brush with egg. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water until dissolved.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Turn 1/2 into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream; add rest of Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate.
Can be served in squares on lettuce leaf.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix well and roll thin. Cut and freeze on a cookie sheet. Place in freezer bags until ready to use. Drop into boiling broth and cook when ready.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 1/2 at a time until browned.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, prepare ramen noodle soup according to package directions.
Add seasoning packet.
Drain noodles.
Serve chicken over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time 10 minutes. Cook time, 20 minutes.
tags: Campbell's chicken flavor ramen noodle soup

title: taco salad
directions: Mix
lettuce,
tomato, grated cheese and chopped olives to make
a
salad.
Brown
hamburger meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning
to
the	hamburger according to package directions. Add meat
to
salad and toss.
Add Fritos to salad just before serving to maintain crispness.

title: frosted liver pate ball
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and form into a ball.
Mix well the last 3 ingredients and frost ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: ham strata
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13 greased pan with cubed bread pieces. Add 1/2 of cubed ham.
Mix the 2 cheeses together and put 1/2 over ham and bread cubes.
Repeat layers.
Slightly beat the eggs and mix with milk, onion salt and seasoned salt.
Pour over layers; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, melt butter.
Add crushed corn flakes to butter; mix well.
Sprinkle over strata. Bake at 50 to 60 minutes in 370° oven.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.
Can also use whatever cheese you have on hand.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs with milk.
Stir together flour and salt; mix with egg mixture until well blended.
Pour some of the fat into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange sausages in the pan and pour batter over the sausages.
Bake about 30 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco and oil until fluffy.
Add buttermilk-soda mixture, coconut and egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and flavoring.
Bake in 3 well-greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough over round pizza pan. Bake it in oven at 250° until golden brown and slightly soft. Allow to cool.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, brown sugar, cereal, apples and walnuts.
Add (blended together) eggs, milk, molasses and shortening or oil.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes in a greased and floured bread pan.

title: sparkling clear window wash
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray on and towel off.
Shine windows with newspapers, if desired.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: unbaked chocolate cake
directions: Put butter in pan and add sugar, cocoa and beaten eggs.
Stir well.
Bring to boil and simmer one minute.
Add vanilla, nuts and crumbs.
Pour into greased 8 inch pan.
Ice with chocolate icing. Keep in refrigerator.
Cut into fingers.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix together beaten egg, milk and juice from clams.
Place dry ingredients in greased loaf pan.
Pour milk mixture over dry ingredients.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with relish, mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Crumble cornbread and add.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello.
Heat, but do not boil.
Mix Cool Whip, buttermilk and pecans until well blended.
Combine two mixtures.
Chill overnight.

title: kate's spuds supreme
directions: Dice peeled, cooked potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbling.
Garnish with cooked chopped bacon and sliced olives.

title: barbecued corn-on-the-cob
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine salsa and parsley.
Preheat barbecue grill (use high setting if cooking with gas grill).
Cut two 12 x 19-inch pieces of aluminum foil.
Place corn in center of each piece and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon half the salsa mixture over each ear of corn; turn corn to coat.
Fold foil to enclose corn.
Place foil packets on preheated grill; cook for 10 minutes, turning every 2 to 3 minutes.
Carefully open foil packets and transfer corn to serving dish; serve immediately.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Cook potatoes in water until tender with seasoning.
Combine onions with potatoes in their water and clams, heating to boiling point.
Add thyme and half and half.
Stir until blended and hot enough to serve.
Do not boil.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Marinate steak 12 hours.
Barbecue or broil steak 7 1/2 minutes on each side.
Slice on the diagonal.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter in pan and pour excess into mixing bowl. Add all other ingredients. Mix and pour into buttered pan and bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put oleo into 8-inch pie pan.
Put into oven until melted.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream. Garnish with shaved Hershey bar.

title: brownie pudding dessert
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk, vanilla and shortening.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter on top.
Pour 1 3/4 cup hot water over and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pudding will form on bottom.

title: german farm bread(deutsches bauernbrot)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in lukewarm water and admit lukewarm milk, salt and rye flour.
Knead the dough well.
Admit wheaten flour until the dough is supple.
Now the dough must rise 45 minutes. After that time form a bread of the dough.
Then let it rise again for 30 minutes.
Dab the bread with coffee, milk or sweet cream. Put the bread in the oven for 45 minutes at 440°.
Then put it on a rust until it is cold.

title: grandad's bourbon balls
directions: Blend bourbon and corn syrup in cup.
In mixing bowl, mix together vanilla wafer crumbs, walnuts, powdered sugar and cocoa powder.
Add bourbon corn syrup mixture to dry ingredients.
With damp hands, form dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and place on plate.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Put in cool place for a day, then store in airtight container.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and dry Jell-O until blended.
Add oil, water and eggs, beating well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer cut up broccoli in water 15 minutes.
Do not drain off water.
Add dry soup mix and 1 cup half and half.
Stir until well mixed.
Add Velveeta cubes.
Stir until melted.
Simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Cauliflower may be substituted.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl; add soda to buttermilk.
Cut in shortening with blender or fork.
Add buttermilk and stir well.
Remove fork and knead lightly to form a smooth dough.
Toss on a lightly floured cloth or board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and place on oiled baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen biscuits.

title: carrot ring
directions: Grease ring mold.
Mix ingredients.
Place in mold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes with mold sitting in pan of water.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Cook in electric skillet on low until desired tenderness. Stir often.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Serve all but bread crumbs over your greens.
Then you sprinkle your salad with bread crumbs, broiled in garlic oil.

title: old-fashioned nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, sour cream and flour together; mix well. Lightly flour pecans and raisins before adding.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in a tube pan and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until light brown.

title: plain rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, fat and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix with enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in well-greased bowl.
Brush with melted butter and cover with cloth. Put bowl in warm place and allow to rise until double in bulk.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish with lid. Add all ingredients. Stir. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt chocolate bar in top of double boiler.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir baking soda into buttermilk.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk into creamed butter mixture.
Add melted chocolate bar, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, not a Bundt pan.
Bake for 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer (do not mix) the lettuce, celery, carrots, green pepper, purple onion, peas and cheese.
Fry bacon crisp; cool and crumble. Add to top of salad.
Spread mayo over salad, then sprinkle sugar over Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Cover and leave 24 hours in refrigerator.
Toss and serve.

title: ranch style potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and dice.
Add onion, celery and sweet relish.
Mix together mayonnaise, salad dressing and milk until creamy.
Pour over potatoes.
Add eggs.
Chill and serve.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreos into fine crumbs.
Soften ice cream and Cool Whip. Mix all ingredients and freeze in pie pans.
(Very good to keep in freezer.)

title: turkey and dressing casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box and set aside.
Place a thin layer of stuffing in a round casserole dish and top with 1/2 can chicken gravy.
With remainder of stuffing, place about 1 tablespoon on each slice of turkey and roll up and place in casserole dish, layering on top of each other.
Then pour remainder of chicken gravy over this and bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown beef and onions in oil in large saucepan.
Add beans, tomatoes, water, chilies, beef broth granules, sugar and garlic. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
To serve, ladle into individual bowls and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with warm tortillas.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar, salt and oleo.
Mix well. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pumpkin, salt, Milnot, and spices. Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract. Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: christmas dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend until smooth. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables (carrots, celery, cauliflower, green peppers or whatever).
Can also serve with crackers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, sugar and flour together.
Add 1 cup milk and eggs (beaten) and mix together.
Then add 1 teaspoon salt and melted oleo.
Add to the creamed corn mixture.
Put in casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, onions and celery. Rinse. Put vegetables in water with margarine and salt. Cook on medium heat for 25 to 40 minutes until soft. Add soup, stir. If soup is too thin you may add potato flakes to thicken as you desire.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix the apples, vinegar and red hots in crock-pot and cook for 4 hours.
Then add the sugar and cook for 8 hours.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon oil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix together remaining cake mix, 1 egg, 1/2 c. butter.
Press into greased 9x13 inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees. While this is baking, mix 2/3 c. cake mix, brown sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, 3 eggs and pecans.
Pour this mixture over the baked crust and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cut into bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits and add orange juice to make 3 cups liquid.
Make pudding as directed using 3 cups fruit juices instead of the 4 cups milk.
Cool.
Add drained fruit.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in large bowl.
Add milk, eggs, butter, potatoes and vanilla.
Stir well, then pour in a large unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake it until it looks firm and beginning to crack around outer edge.

title: party punch
directions: Combine pineapple, orange, lemon juice. Mix sugar before serving.
Add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add lemon jello and cream cheese.
Let set to cool.
Add Cool Whip and chill until set.
Yum.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top. Refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: apple, pineapple, orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a saucepan. Add margarine and lemon juice; cook over medium heat until margarine is melted. Mix cornstarch and water until smooth. Add to juice mixture. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes. Reduce heat. Add sweetener and cool to room temperature. Pour over the fruit. Toss to coat. Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: pretty salad
directions: Steam cauliflower, broccoli and carrots for 3 or 4 minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Mix with Italian dressing to taste.

title: blueberry buckle coffee cake
directions: Wash blueberries and strain.
Stir together sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in milk and add flour.
Fold blueberries in and pour into a greased tube pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle on cake top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix Karo syrup and peanut butter in a small bowl.
Stir in gradually nonfat dry milk and confectioners sugar.
Shape into roll about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Roll may be decorated with chopped nuts.
Chill; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 24.

title: vichyssoise or potato leek soup
directions: Chop onions and white part of leeks finely and saute in small amount of chicken broth.
Add finely chopped potatoes, remainder of broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer until the potatoes are tender.
Add milk and heat until hot, but not boiling.
Blend mixture until smooth.
Check seasonings and adjust if necessary. May be served hot or cold.
For a richer soup, add butter and cream.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight fitting lid and shake.
Or blend in blender.
Yields 1 cup.

title: squash bake
directions: Cook squash and carrots until tender and drain.
Chop onion and celery. Saute in butter or margarine until tender.
Mash first 4 ingredients. Blend the rest of the ingredients.
Spray dish or pan with Pam.
Pour in pan.
Crumble 3 slices of bread and sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine, butter or spray Pam on top. Sprinkle garlic powder. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, chestnuts, cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Bake in a lightly greased casserole dish at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with melted margarine and bake until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly but well. Mix flour mixture to wet mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° until done; remove from pans.
Cool.

title: rocks
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then eggs.
Put soda in sour milk.
Add cinnamon and salt to flour.
Add flour to butter mixture, alternately with sour milk.
Add oatmeal, then raisins and vanilla.
Put on cookie sheet in spoonfuls.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Put cherries and sugar in a pan and bring to a boil; add Jell-O and stir until gelatin is dissolved; add pineapple and nuts.
Add cola.
Pour into oiled dish (mold) and refrigerate until set.
(If you like, soften cream cheese and add after gelatin is dissolved.)

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strudel
directions: Cut butter into flour; add sour cream and form dough into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into 4 parts and roll each into rectangle on floured surface.
Spread with preserves; sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Slice and serve.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Heat margarine and oil in a 9 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish in 400° oven until margarine is melted.
Place chicken in dish, turn to coat and arrange skin side up.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix soup, mushrooms (with liquid), water, thyme and Worcestershire sauce.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter; stir in cocoa.
Add eggs, sugar, flour and salt to melted mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Work ingredients into smooth dough.
Divide.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough on board covered with powdered sugar.
Cut in squares or circles; put in filling and fold over, pressing edges together with fork.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic.
Spread on bread halves.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Wrap each half in foil.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours, or freeze.
Unwrap and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes (20 to 25 minutes, if frozen).
Cut into slices.
Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Chill all ingredients and add 1 quart ginger ale; pour over ice.

title: sally ann cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill batter.
Roll out and cut with empty spam can.
Bake in moderate oven and frost with the following:
Soak 1 package Knox unflavored gelatine in 1 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup sugar and stir in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, simmer 10 minutes.
Pour syrup into 1 3/4 cup powdered sugar and beat.
Add 3/4 teaspoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat about 15 minutes or until thick.
Frost bottom of cookies.
Let dry.

title: chocoffee drink
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 to 4 heaped teaspoonfuls for 1 cup of boiling water.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Shape into rolls on waxed paper and chill.
Slice and bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Bring water, oil and butter or margarine to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture and beat until foamy.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper and rice.
Drain.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the rice gets tender.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
With spoon, make a deep well in the center and all the ingredients.
Stir carefully, just enough to dampen all the dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Slice and spread with a mixture of 3 ounces of cream cheese and 3 ounces of butter.
May be used as a dessert.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: japanese fruit cake(this recipe makes six thin layers!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Set aside 1/2 the batter.
Take the other half batter and bake 3 layers (8 or 9-inch round pans) at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
(Watch - ovens vary!!)
Add the raisins, nuts, cloves and cinnamon to the set aside batter.
Bake these 3 layers the same way as others.

title: frozen chocolate mousse
directions: Combine graham cracker and margarine; press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Beat together chocolate, egg, and vanilla; stir in pecans.
Reserve 1 cup whipped cream; blend remaining into chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually beat in sugar until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture; pour into prepared crust.
Garnish with reserved whipped cream.
Cover; freeze 6 hours or overnight.

title: apple rolls
directions: Melt butter.
In a bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, melted butter, 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, egg and whole wheat flour.
Stir to blend.
Add the all-purpose flour.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in a warm place for about 40 minutes.
Punch down.
Peel apples. Cut into wedges.
On a floured board, knead dough until satiny. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each out to a rectangle.
Cut each rectangle into 10 squares.
Place 1 apple wedge in the middle of each square.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over apple wedges.
Fold dough over apples to cover completely.
Place on a greased baking sheet, seam-side down. Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
Increase temperature to 425° and bake for another 4 minutes until golden brown.
Cool, covered, on wire rack. Serve with coffee or tea.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and stuffing.
Spoon half of stuffing into shallow casserole and cover with chicken.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Flour fruit. Sift dry ingredients together. Combine all. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° about 35 minutes. Cool briefly and place on racks to cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bundles
directions: Thaw pastry for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to a 12-inch square.
Cut into four (6-inch) squares.
In the center of each square, place 1/4 cup chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon walnuts.
Bring pastry corners together just above chocolate; twist and turn.
Fan out corners.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand at least 10 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.

title: molded lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While hot, beat cheese into boiling mixture with egg beater until foamy. When cool, add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Add whipping cream and sugar.
Pour into salad mold. Serves 8.

title: molded gelatin
directions: To cooled gelatin, add all other ingredients.
Pour in oblong pan.
Cut and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles with 1/2 teaspoon salt and vegetable oil; when noodles are done, drain and put in cold water.
While noodles boil, fry hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain.

Put hamburger in a saucepan and add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, parsley, oregano, crushed basil, sugar (or grape jelly) and bay leaf; bring to a boil and let simmer for at least 20 minutes (the longer it simmers the better the sauce).

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, mayonnaise, celery, onion, apple, almonds, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Spread on rolls or croissants.

title: creamy orange dip
directions: In small bowl; combine all ingredients except fruit; mix well. Chill 1 hour to blend flavors.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: casserole for a crowd
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
